{"title_page": "European route E20", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Infobox road\n| country     = EUR\n| type        = E\n| route       = 20\n| map         = \n| direction_a = West\n| terminus_a  = [[Shannon Airport]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n| junction    =\n| direction_b = East\n| terminus_b  = [[Saint Petersburg]], [[Russia]]\n| countries   = {{flag|Ireland}}<br>{{flag|United Kingdom}}<br>{{flag|Denmark}}<br>{{flag|Sweden}}<br>{{flag|Estonia}}<br>{{flag|Russia}}\n}}\n'''European route E20''' is a part of the [[United Nations]] [[International E-road network]]. It runs roughly west\u2013east through [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]], the [[United Kingdom]], [[Denmark]], [[Sweden]], [[Estonia]], and [[Russia]]. \n\nIts length is {{convert|1880|km|mi|abbr=on}} but it is not continuous; at three points, a sea crossing is required. [[Roll-on/roll-off]] ferries make the crossings from [[Dublin]] to [[Liverpool]] and from [[Stockholm]] to [[Tallinn]]. No publicly accessible ferries traverse the [[North Sea]] from [[Kingston-upon-Hull]] to [[Esbjerg]] (as of 2019), but a ferry for commercial drivers leaves [[Immingham]] for Esbjerg on most days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfds.com/en-gb/freight-shipping/routes-and-schedules/esbjerg-immingham|title=DFDS|website=www.dfds.com|access-date=2019-05-25}}</ref>\n\n== Route ==\n=== Ireland ===\nThe initial section of the E20 from [[Shannon Airport]] to Dublin via [[Limerick]] is approximately 228&nbsp;km long and is only partially signed, along the M7/N7. The section from Shannon Airport to east of Limerick is mainly [[dual carriageway]], with a short section of [[motorway]] as part of the Limerick Southern Ring Road. The [[Shannon Tunnel]], opened on 16 July 2010, completed the [[Bypass (road)|bypass]] of Limerick. The section from Limerick to [[Naas]] is motorway (M7), and the final section from Naas to Dublin is dual carriageway (N7). A ferry must be used from Dublin to Liverpool.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.poferries.com/en/dublin-liverpool|title=Dublin to Liverpool Ferry {{!}} Ferries to Liverpool {{!}} P&O Ferries - UK|website=www.poferries.com|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n\n=== United Kingdom ===\nE20 follows the A5080 from [[Liverpool]] to [[Huyton]], the [[M62 motorway|M62]] from [[Huyton]] to [[South Cave]], and the [[A63 road|A63]] from [[South Cave]] to [[Kingston upon Hull]]. The route length across the UK is {{convert|205|km|mi}} in total but is not signposted.\n\nThere are no ferries between Kingston upon Hull and [[Esbjerg]]. Alternative ferries were once available from [[Immingham]], which is {{convert|48|km|mi}} from Kingston upon Hull, and [[Harwich]], which is {{convert|350|km|mi}} from Kingston upon Hull. There are no longer any passenger routes operating between the UK and Scandinavia.\n\nThe closest alternative is to take the [[Eurotunnel Shuttle]] from [[Cheriton, Kent|Cheriton]] (Folkestone) to [[Calais]], or take a ferry from [[Harwich]] to [[Hook of Holland]]. Both of these routes would require a detour of around 900 miles (940 miles to Esbjerg, as this route would require you to drive along the E20 to reach Esbjerg).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Kingston+upon+Hull,+Hull/Esbjerg,+Denmark/@53.1347163,0.1042165,6z/|title=Hull to Esbjerg|website=Hull to Esbjerg|language=en|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n\n=== Denmark ===\nIn Denmark, E20 is a motorway from [[Esbjerg]] to the [[\u00d8resund Bridge]]. The length of the Danish part is {{convert|315|km|mi|abbr=on}}.\n\nIt passes first along [[Jutland]] from Esbjerg to [[Kolding]], then crosses the [[Little Belt Bridge]] onto [[Funen]]. E20 crosses the entirety of Funen, passing around 2km from Odense. Then, at [[Nyborg]], E20 crosses the [[Great Belt Fixed Link]] onto [[Zealand]]. E20 follows the Vestmotorvejen until [[K\u00f8ge]], where it goes north to Copenhagen. In Copenhagen, E20 passes south of the city, crossing onto [[Kastrup]] where it meets the [[Copenhagen Airport]]. The \u00d8resund Bridge begins as a tunnel on Kastrup.\n\nBetween [[K\u00f8ge]] and [[Copenhagen]], the road has three E-road numbers ([[European route E47|E47]] and [[European route E55|E55]]).\n\nThe Great Belt Bridge and \u00d8resund Bridge are both tolled, charging over \u20ac30 each.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dk.oresundsbron.com/page/1053|title=\u00d8resundsbron|author=|date=|website=dk.oresundsbron.com|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.storebaelt.dk/priserprodukter/priser/biler|title=Personbil - Storeb\u00e6lt|author=|date=|website=www.storebaelt.dk|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref> The road crosses the border between Denmark and Sweden on the \u00d8resund Bridge.<!-- {{hidden begin|border=1px #aaa solid|title={{center|List of exits (east to west)}}}}\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]15 [[Copenhagen Airport|Lufthavn \u00d8]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]16 [[Copenhagen Airport|Lufthavn]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]17 [[Copenhagen Airport|Lufthavn V]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]18 [[T\u00e5rnby]] {{Riksvei|221}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]19 [[\u00d8restad]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]20 [[Copenhagen|K\u00f8benhavn C]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]21 [[Aved\u00f8re Holme]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]22 [[Gl. K\u00f8ge Landevej]] {{Riksvei|151}}\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{Europavei|47|n}} {{Europavei|55|n}} [[Helsing\u00f8r]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]25 [[Br\u00f8ndbyvester]] {{DRNSs|O3}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]26 [[Ish\u00f8j Strand]] {{Riksvei|243}}\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{DRNSs|O4|n}} [[Lyngby]], [[Roskilde]], [[Copenhagen]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]27 [[Greve Strand|Greve N]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]28 [[Greve Strand|Greve C]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]29 [[Greve Strand|Greve S]] {{Riksvei|217}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] | [[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] Karlsunde\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]30 [[Solr\u00f8d|Solr\u00f8d N]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]31 [[Solr\u00f8d|Solr\u00f8d S]] {{DRNSs|6}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]32 [[K\u00f8ge]]\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{Europavei|47|s}} {{Europavei|55|s}} [[R\u00f8dby]], [[Gedser]]\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]| Salby\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]33 [[Vemmedrup]]\n*|[[File:Zeichen 377.svg|20px]] Bj\u00e6verskov\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]34 [[Borup, K\u00f8ge Municipality|Borup]]\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] Kongsted/B\u00f8gede\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] Kv\u00e6rkeby\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]35 [[Ringsted|Ringsted \u00d8]] {{DRNSs|14}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]36 [[Ringsted|Ringsted N]] {{Riksvei|215|n}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] | [[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] Tuels\u00f8\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]37 [[Sor\u00f8]] {{DRNSs|57}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]38 [[Slagelse|Slagelse \u00d8]] {{Riksvei|150}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] Antvorskov\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]39 [[Slagelse|Slagelse S]] {{DRNSs|22}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]40 [[Vemmelev]] {{Riksvei|150}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]41 [[Tj\u00e6reby]] {{Riksvei|277}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]42 [[Kors\u00f8r]] {{Riksvei|265|s}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]43 [[Halskov]] [[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]44 [[Knudshoved]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]45 [[Nyborg|Nyborg \u00d8]] {{Riksvei|153|s}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]46 [[Nyborg|Nyborg V]] {{Riksvei|165|n}} {{DRNSs|8|s}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] R\u00f8nninge\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]47 [[Langeskov]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]48 [[Tietgenbyen]]\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{DRNSs|9|n}} [[Svendborg]] {{DRNSs|9|s}} [[Odense]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]50 [[Hjallese]] {{Riksvei|167|s}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]51 [[Odense|Odense S]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]52 [[Odense|Odense SV]] {{Riksvei|168}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]53 [[Odense|Odense V]] {{Riksvei|161}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] | [[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] Kildebjerg\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]54 [[Vissenbjerg]] {{Riksvei|335}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]55 [[Aarup]] {{Riksvei|329}}\n*|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] \u00c5lsbo\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]56 [[Ejby, Middelfart Municipality|Ejby]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]57 [[N\u00f8rre \u00c5by]] {{Riksvei|313}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] Lilleb\u00e6lt\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]58 [[Middelfart]] [[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]59 [[Fredericia|Fredericia S]] {{DRNSs|28|n}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]60 [[Fredericia|Fredericia V]] {{Riksvei|171}}\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{Europavei|45|n}} [[Horsens]], [[\u00c5rhus]], [[Aalborg]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]61 [[Taulov]]\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{Europavei|45|s}} [[Kolding]], [[Aabenraa]], [[Flensburg]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]62 [[Kolding|Kolding \u00d8]] {{Riksvei|176|v}}{{Riksvei|170}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]63 [[Bramdrupdam]]\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{Europavei|45|s}} [[Aabenraa]], [[Flensburg]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]64 [[Kolding|Kolding V]]\n*[[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] Harte\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]65 [[Lunderskov|Lunderskov \u00d8]] {{DRNSs|32|s}}{{Riksvei|191|s}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]66 [[Lunderskov]] {{Riksvei|469}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]67 [[Vejen|Vejen \u00d8]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]68 [[Vejen]] {{Riksvei|403|s}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]69 [[Br\u00f8rup]] {{Riksvei|417}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]70 [[Holsted]] {{Riksvei|425}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] Bj\u00f8vlund\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]71 [[G\u00f8rding]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]72 [[Bramming]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]73 [[Korskro]] {{DRNSs|11}}{{DRNSs|30|n}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]74 [[Skads]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]75 [[Esbjerg|Esbjerg N]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]76 [[Esbjerg|Esbjerg \u00d8]]\n{{div col end}}\n{{hidden end}}\n -->\n\n=== Sweden ===\nIn Sweden, E20 is a motorway from the [[\u00d6resund Bridge]] in [[Malm\u00f6]] to N\u00e4\u00e4s 30&nbsp;km east of [[Gothenburg]], a {{convert|320|km|mi|abbr=on}} long motorway. Furthermore, it is a motorway most of the route from Vretstorp (20&nbsp;km (12&nbsp;mi) west of [[\u00d6rebro]]) to [[Stockholm]].\n\nThe Swedish part of E20 is {{convert|770|km|mi|abbr=on}} long. Its extent is shared with [[European route E6|E6]] along a {{convert|280|km|mi|abbr=on}} long stretch, with [[European route E18|E18]] along {{convert|50|km|mi|abbr=on}} and with [[European route E4|E4]] along {{convert|35|km|mi|abbr=on}}.\n\nThe part through Stockholm has very heavy traffic, including the most heavily trafficked road in Scandinavia{{Citation needed|date=June 2010}}, [[Essingeleden]] (160&nbsp;000 vehicles/day). There is often congestion on this stretch. A new tunnel for route E20, \"[[Norra l\u00e4nken]]\", was built north of the city center and opened 30 November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trafikverket.se/Privat/Projekt/Stockholm/E20-norra-lanken/Om_projektet/|title=Om projektet Norra l\u00e4nken|first=|last=Trafikverket|date=|website=Trafikverket|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref> The planned [[F\u00f6rbifart Stockholm]] bypass will divert traffic from Essingeleden.{{citation needed|date=April 2013}}\n\nBetween [[Stockholm]] and [[Tallinn]] a car ferry departs daily, taking 15 hours. The port in Stockholm is located at [[Lilla V\u00e4rtan]], about 4&nbsp;km northeast of the central core of the city.\n\n=== Estonia ===\nIn Estonia, E20 follows the route of national [[Transport in Estonia#National roads|main road]] nr. 1 (Tallinn\u2013Narva). In Tallinn to relieve traffic a bridge has been built on the intersection of the [[European route E263|E263]] and the E20. The E20 across Estonia is partially an unsigned expressway (speed limit 110&nbsp;km/h in summer), for 80.7&nbsp;km east of Tallinn to [[Aaspere]] along with a section near Haljala (km 87 - 90.5) and a section between [[Kohtla-J\u00e4rve]] and [[J\u00f5hvi]] (km 155.9\u2013163.2). The remainder being single carriageway. The distance from Tallinn to the Russian border at the [[Narva River]] is 218&nbsp;km.\n\n=== Russia ===\nIn Russia, the route takes the Narva Highway (also listed in the Russian road numbering system as the [[A180 highway (Russia)|A180 route]], formerly known as the M11 route) running from [[Ivangorod]] to [[Saint Petersburg]] as a dual-lane highway. The distance from Ivangorod to Saint Petersburg is 142&nbsp;km.\n\nThe border control facilities at the Estonia-Russia crossing are equipped and being operated for a limited amount of traffic on both sides of the border. The border crossing requires a reservation - despite this, waiting lines still can extend for many hours and even days.<ref>{{Cite web\n| title = Electronic reservation system for border crossings at the Estonia-Russia checkpoints; updates on the waiting lines. | url = https://www.eestipiir.ee/yphis/index.action}}</ref>\n\n{{gallery\n|title =E20 route, west to east\n|File:M62 motorway, Calderdale.jpg|The M62 passes [[Scammonden Reservoir]] in [[West Yorkshire]]\n|File:E20 53.jpg|E&nbsp;20 near [[Odense]], [[Denmark]]\n|File:Copenhagen airport from air.jpg|E20 next to the [[Copenhagen Airport]]\n|File:\u00d6resundsbron i solnedg\u00e5ng 2.jpg|[[Oresund Bridge]], between [[Denmark]] and [[Sweden]]\n|File:\u00d6resundsbrons vajrar 2.jpg|On Oresund Bridge\n|File:Landskrona, 2006-09-11.jpg|East coast of Oresund, between [[Malm\u00f6]] and [[Helsingborg]], showing the city of [[Landskrona]].\n|File:Tallinn-Narva maantee.jpg|Near [[J\u00e4gala]], Estonia\n||Border between [[Narva]] (Estonia) (left) and [[Ivangorod]] (Russia)\n}}\n\n== Itinerary ==\n*{{flag|Ireland}}\n**{{jct|country=IRL|N|18}}: [[Shannon, County Clare|Shannon]] - [[Limerick]]\n**{{jct|country=IRL|M|7}}: [[Limerick]] - [[Borris-in-Ossory]] ({{BAB-E|201|IE}}) - [[Portlaoise]] - [[Naas]]\n**{{jct|country=IRL|N|7}}: [[Naas]] - [[Dublin]]\n**{{jct|country=IRL|M|50}}: [[Dublin]]\n*Gap ([[Irish Sea]])\n**[[File:Ferry Sign.svg|20px|link=Ferry]]: {{flagicon|Ireland}} [[Dublin]] - {{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[Liverpool]]\n*{{flag|United Kingdom}}\n**{{jct|country=GBR|A|5036}}: [[Bootle]]\n**{{jct|country=GBR|M|57}}: '''[[Liverpool]]''' Outer Ring Road (''Whole length'')\n**{{jct|country=GBR|M|62}}: [[Huyton]] - '''[[Manchester]]''' (Interchange with {{BAB-E|5}} and start of multiplex with {{BAB-E|22}} at [[File:UK-Motorway-M6.svg|x15px|link=M6 motorway]] [[Warrington]])\n**{{jct|country=GBR|M|60}}: '''[[Manchester]]''' Outer Ring Road (''Clockwise'')\n**{{jct|country=GBR|M|62}}: '''[[Manchester]]''' - [[File:UK road A63.svg|40px|link=A63 road]] (Interchange with {{BAB-E|15}} at [[File:UK-Motorway-A1(M).svg|x15px|link=A1(M) motorway]] [[Pontefract]] and end of multiplex with {{BAB-E|22}} at [[File:UK-Motorway-M18.svg|x15px|link=M18 motorway]] [[Goole]])\n**{{jct|country=GBR|A|63}}: [[File:UK-Motorway-M62.svg|x15px|link=M62 motorway]] - [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]]\n**{{jct|country=GBR|A|1033}}: [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]]\n*Gap ([[North Sea]])\n**{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]] - {{flagicon|Denmark}} [[Esbjerg]]\n*{{flag|Denmark}}\n**{{BAB-E|20|DK}}: [[Esbjerg]] - [[Kolding]] ({{BAB-E|45|DK}}) - [[K\u00f8ge]] (Start of Concurrency with {{BAB-E|47|DK}} {{BAB-E|55|DK}}) - [[K\u00f8benhavn]] (End of Concurrency with {{BAB-E|47|DK}} {{BAB-E|55|DK}})\n*{{flag|Sweden}}\n**{{BAB-E|20|S}}: [[Malm\u00f6]] ({{jct|country=SWE|E|22|E|65|rdt=y}}, Start of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|6|rdt=y}}) - [[Helsingborg]] ({{jct|country=SWE|E|4|rdt=y}}) - [[Gothenburg]] ({{jct|country=SWE|E|45|rdt=y}}, End of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|6|rdt=y}}) - [[\u00d6rebro]] (Start of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|18|rdt=y}}) - [[Arboga]] (End of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|18|rdt=y}}) - [[Eskilstuna]] - [[S\u00f6dert\u00e4lje]] (Start of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|4|rdt=y}}) - [[Stockholm]] (End of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|4|rdt=y}}, Towards {{jct|country=SWE|E|18|rdt=y}})\n*Gap ([[Baltic Sea]])\n**[[File:Ferry Sign.svg|20px|link=Ferry]]: {{flagicon|Sweden}} [[Stockholm]] - {{flagicon|Estonia}} [[Tallinn]]\n*{{flag|Estonia}}\n**J\u00f5e, Narva maantee, Tartu maantee: [[Tallinn]] ({{BAB-E|67|EE}})\n**{{jct|country=EST|N|1}}: [[Tallinn]] ({{BAB-E|67|EE}} {{BAB-E|263|EE}} {{BAB-E|265|EE}}) - [[J\u00f5hvi]] ({{BAB-E|264|EE}}) - [[Narva]]\n*{{flag|Russia}}\n**{{jct|country=RUS|A|180}}: [[Ivangorod]] - [[Saint Petersburg]] (Towards {{BAB-E|18|RUS}} {{BAB-E|95|RUS}} {{BAB-E|105|RUS}})\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|E20}}\n{{E-road}}\n\n[[Category:International E-road network|20]]\n[[Category:European routes in the United Kingdom|20]]\n[[Category:Roads in Denmark|E020]]\n[[Category:Roads in England|2-0020]]\n[[Category:Roads in Estonia|E020]]\n[[Category:European routes in Ireland|E020]]\n[[Category:European routes in Russia|E20]]\n[[Category:Motorways in Sweden|E020]]\n[[Category:Roads in Lancashire|2-0020]]\n[[Category:Roads in Yorkshire|2-0020]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Infobox road\n| country     = EUR\n| type        = E\n| route       = 20\n| map         = \n| direction_a = West\n| terminus_a  = [[Shannon Airport]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n| junction    =\n| direction_b = East\n| terminus_b  = [[Saint Petersburg]], [[Russia]]\n| countries   = {{flag|Ireland}}<br>{{flag|United Kingdom}}<br>{{flag|Denmark}}<br>{{flag|Sweden}}<br>{{flag|Estonia}}<br>{{flag|Russia}}\n}}\n'''European route E20''' is a part of the [[United Nations]] [[International E-road network]]. It runs roughly west\u2013east through [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]], the [[United Kingdom]], [[Denmark]], [[Sweden]], [[Estonia]], and [[Russia]]. \n\nIts length is {{convert|1880|km|mi|abbr=on}} but it is not continuous; at three points, a sea crossing is required. [[Roll-on/roll-off]] ferries make the crossings from [[Dublin]] to [[Liverpool]] and from [[Stockholm]] to [[Tallinn]]. No publicly accessible ferries traverse the [[North Sea]] from [[Kingston-upon-Hull]] to [[Esbjerg]] (as of 2019), but a ferry for commercial drivers leaves [[Immingham]] for Esbjerg on most days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfds.com/en-gb/freight-shipping/routes-and-schedules/esbjerg-immingham|title=DFDS|website=www.dfds.com|access-date=2019-05-25}}</ref>\n\n== Route ==\n=== Ireland ===\nThe initial section of the E20 from [[Shannon Airport]] to Dublin via [[Limerick]] is approximately 228&nbsp;km long and is only partially signed, along the M7/N7. The section from Shannon Airport to east of Limerick is mainly [[dual carriageway]], with a short section of [[motorway]] as part of the Limerick Southern Ring Road. The [[Shannon Tunnel]], opened on 16 July 2010, completed the [[Bypass (road)|bypass]] of Limerick. The section from Limerick to [[Naas]] is motorway (M7), and the final section from Naas to Dublin is dual carriageway (N7). A ferry must be used from Dublin to Liverpool.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.poferries.com/en/dublin-liverpool|title=Dublin to Liverpool Ferry {{!}} Ferries to Liverpool {{!}} P&O Ferries - UK|website=www.poferries.com|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n\n=== United Kingdom ===\nE20 follows the A5080 from [[Liverpool]] to [[Huyton]], the [[M62 motorway|M62]] from [[Huyton]] to [[South Cave]], and the [[A63 road|A63]] from [[South Cave]] to [[Kingston upon Hull]]. The route length across the UK is {{convert|205|km|mi}} in total but is not signposted.\n\nThere are no ferries between Kingston upon Hull and [[Esbjerg]]. Alternative ferries were once available from [[Immingham]], which is {{convert|48|km|mi}} from Kingston upon Hull, and [[Harwich]], which is {{convert|350|km|mi}} from Kingston upon Hull. There are no longer any passenger routes operating between the UK and Scandinavia.\n\nThe closest alternative is to take the [[Eurotunnel Shuttle]] from [[Cheriton, Kent|Cheriton]] (Folkestone) to [[Calais]], or take a ferry from [[Harwich]] to [[Hook of Holland]]. Both of these routes would require a detour of around 900 miles (940 miles to Esbjerg, as this route would require you to drive along the E20 to reach Esbjerg).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Kingston+upon+Hull,+Hull/Esbjerg,+Denmark/@53.1347163,0.1042165,6z/|title=Hull to Esbjerg|website=Hull to Esbjerg|language=en|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n\n=== Denmark ===\nIn Denmark, E20 is a motorway from [[Esbjerg]] to the [[\u00d8resund Bridge]]. The length of the Danish part is {{convert|315|km|mi|abbr=on}}.\n\nIt passes first along [[Jutland]] from Esbjerg to [[Kolding]], then crosses the [[Little Belt Bridge]] onto [[Funen]]. E20 crosses the entirety of Funen, passing around 2km from Odense. Then, at [[Nyborg]], E20 crosses the [[Great Belt Fixed Link]] onto [[Zealand]]. E20 follows the Vestmotorvejen until [[K\u00f8ge]], where it goes north to Copenhagen. In Copenhagen, E20 passes south of the city, crossing onto [[Kastrup]] where it meets the [[Copenhagen Airport]]. The \u00d8resund Bridge begins as a tunnel on Kastrup.\n\nBetween [[K\u00f8ge]] and [[Copenhagen]], the road has three E-road numbers ([[European route E47|E47]] and [[European route E55|E55]]).\n\nThe Great Belt Bridge and \u00d8resund Bridge are both tolled, charging over \u20ac30 each.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dk.oresundsbron.com/page/1053|title=\u00d8resundsbron|author=|date=|website=dk.oresundsbron.com|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.storebaelt.dk/priserprodukter/priser/biler|title=Personbil - Storeb\u00e6lt|author=|date=|website=www.storebaelt.dk|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref> The road crosses the border between Denmark and Sweden on the \u00d8resund Bridge.<!-- {{hidden begin|border=1px #aaa solid|title={{center|List of exits (east to west)}}}}\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]15 [[Copenhagen Airport|Lufthavn \u00d8]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]16 [[Copenhagen Airport|Lufthavn]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]17 [[Copenhagen Airport|Lufthavn V]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]18 [[T\u00e5rnby]] {{Riksvei|221}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]19 [[\u00d8restad]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]20 [[Copenhagen|K\u00f8benhavn C]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]21 [[Aved\u00f8re Holme]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]22 [[Gl. K\u00f8ge Landevej]] {{Riksvei|151}}\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{Europavei|47|n}} {{Europavei|55|n}} [[Helsing\u00f8r]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]25 [[Br\u00f8ndbyvester]] {{DRNSs|O3}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]26 [[Ish\u00f8j Strand]] {{Riksvei|243}}\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{DRNSs|O4|n}} [[Lyngby]], [[Roskilde]], [[Copenhagen]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]27 [[Greve Strand|Greve N]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]28 [[Greve Strand|Greve C]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]29 [[Greve Strand|Greve S]] {{Riksvei|217}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] | [[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] Karlsunde\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]30 [[Solr\u00f8d|Solr\u00f8d N]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]31 [[Solr\u00f8d|Solr\u00f8d S]] {{DRNSs|6}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]32 [[K\u00f8ge]]\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{Europavei|47|s}} {{Europavei|55|s}} [[R\u00f8dby]], [[Gedser]]\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]| Salby\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]33 [[Vemmedrup]]\n*|[[File:Zeichen 377.svg|20px]] Bj\u00e6verskov\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]34 [[Borup, K\u00f8ge Municipality|Borup]]\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] Kongsted/B\u00f8gede\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] Kv\u00e6rkeby\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]35 [[Ringsted|Ringsted \u00d8]] {{DRNSs|14}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]36 [[Ringsted|Ringsted N]] {{Riksvei|215|n}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] | [[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] Tuels\u00f8\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]37 [[Sor\u00f8]] {{DRNSs|57}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]38 [[Slagelse|Slagelse \u00d8]] {{Riksvei|150}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] Antvorskov\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]39 [[Slagelse|Slagelse S]] {{DRNSs|22}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]40 [[Vemmelev]] {{Riksvei|150}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]41 [[Tj\u00e6reby]] {{Riksvei|277}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]42 [[Kors\u00f8r]] {{Riksvei|265|s}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]43 [[Halskov]] [[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]44 [[Knudshoved]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]45 [[Nyborg|Nyborg \u00d8]] {{Riksvei|153|s}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]46 [[Nyborg|Nyborg V]] {{Riksvei|165|n}} {{DRNSs|8|s}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] R\u00f8nninge\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]47 [[Langeskov]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]48 [[Tietgenbyen]]\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{DRNSs|9|n}} [[Svendborg]] {{DRNSs|9|s}} [[Odense]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]50 [[Hjallese]] {{Riksvei|167|s}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]51 [[Odense|Odense S]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]52 [[Odense|Odense SV]] {{Riksvei|168}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]53 [[Odense|Odense V]] {{Riksvei|161}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] | [[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] Kildebjerg\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]54 [[Vissenbjerg]] {{Riksvei|335}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]55 [[Aarup]] {{Riksvei|329}}\n*|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] \u00c5lsbo\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]56 [[Ejby, Middelfart Municipality|Ejby]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]57 [[N\u00f8rre \u00c5by]] {{Riksvei|313}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] Lilleb\u00e6lt\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]58 [[Middelfart]] [[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]59 [[Fredericia|Fredericia S]] {{DRNSs|28|n}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]60 [[Fredericia|Fredericia V]] {{Riksvei|171}}\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{Europavei|45|n}} [[Horsens]], [[\u00c5rhus]], [[Aalborg]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]61 [[Taulov]]\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{Europavei|45|s}} [[Kolding]], [[Aabenraa]], [[Flensburg]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]62 [[Kolding|Kolding \u00d8]] {{Riksvei|176|v}}{{Riksvei|170}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]63 [[Bramdrupdam]]\n*[[File:AB-Kreuz-blau.svg]] {{Europavei|45|s}} [[Aabenraa]], [[Flensburg]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]64 [[Kolding|Kolding V]]\n*[[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 361-50.svg|20px]][[File:Zeichen 376.svg|20px]] Harte\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]65 [[Lunderskov|Lunderskov \u00d8]] {{DRNSs|32|s}}{{Riksvei|191|s}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]66 [[Lunderskov]] {{Riksvei|469}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]67 [[Vejen|Vejen \u00d8]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]68 [[Vejen]] {{Riksvei|403|s}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]69 [[Br\u00f8rup]] {{Riksvei|417}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]70 [[Holsted]] {{Riksvei|425}}\n*[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]]|[[File:Zeichen 314 - Parkplatz, StVO 2013.svg|20px]] Bj\u00f8vlund\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]71 [[G\u00f8rding]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]72 [[Bramming]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]73 [[Korskro]] {{DRNSs|11}}{{DRNSs|30|n}}\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]74 [[Skads]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]75 [[Esbjerg|Esbjerg N]]\n*[[File:AB-AS.svg]]76 [[Esbjerg|Esbjerg \u00d8]]\n{{div col end}}\n{{hidden end}}\n -->\n\n=== Sweden ===\nIn Sweden, E20 is a motorway from the [[\u00d6resund Bridge]] in [[Malm\u00f6]] to N\u00e4\u00e4s 30&nbsp;km east of [[Gothenburg]], a {{convert|320|km|mi|abbr=on}} long motorway. Furthermore, it is a motorway most of the route from Vretstorp (20&nbsp;km (12&nbsp;mi) west of [[\u00d6rebro]]) to [[Stockholm]].\n\nThe Swedish part of E20 is {{convert|770|km|mi|abbr=on}} long. Its extent is shared with [[European route E6|E6]] along a {{convert|280|km|mi|abbr=on}} long stretch, with [[European route E18|E18]] along {{convert|50|km|mi|abbr=on}} and with [[European route E4|E4]] along {{convert|35|km|mi|abbr=on}}.\n\nThe part through Stockholm has very heavy traffic, including the most heavily trafficked road in Scandinavia{{Citation needed|date=June 2010}}, [[Essingeleden]] (160&nbsp;000 vehicles/day). There is often congestion on this stretch. A new tunnel for route E20, \"[[Norra l\u00e4nken]]\", was built north of the city center and opened 30 November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trafikverket.se/Privat/Projekt/Stockholm/E20-norra-lanken/Om_projektet/|title=Om projektet Norra l\u00e4nken|first=|last=Trafikverket|date=|website=Trafikverket|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref> The planned [[F\u00f6rbifart Stockholm]] bypass will divert traffic from Essingeleden.{{citation needed|date=April 2013}}\n\nBetween [[Stockholm]] and [[Tallinn]] a car ferry departs daily, taking 15 hours. The port in Stockholm is located at [[Lilla V\u00e4rtan]], about 4&nbsp;km northeast of the central core of the city.\n\n=== Estonia ===\nIn Estonia, E20 follows the route of national [[Transport in Estonia#National roads|main road]] nr. 1 (Tallinn\u2013Narva). In Tallinn to relieve traffic a bridge has been built on the intersection of the [[European route E263|E263]] and the E20. The E20 across Estonia is partially an unsigned expressway (speed limit 110&nbsp;km/h in summer), for 80.7&nbsp;km east of Tallinn to [[Aaspere]] along with a section near Haljala (km 87 - 90.5) and a section between [[Kohtla-J\u00e4rve]] and [[J\u00f5hvi]] (km 155.9\u2013163.2). The remainder being single carriageway. The distance from Tallinn to the Russian border at the [[Narva River]] is 218&nbsp;km.\n\n=== Russia ===\nIn Russia, the route takes the Narva Highway (also listed in the Russian road numbering system as the [[A180 highway (Russia)|A180 route]], formerly known as the M11 route) running from [[Ivangorod]] to [[Saint Petersburg]] as a dual-lane highway. The distance from Ivangorod to Saint Petersburg is 142&nbsp;km.\n\nThe border control facilities at the Estonia-Russia crossing are equipped and being operated for a limited amount of traffic on both sides of the border. The border crossing requires a reservation - despite this, waiting lines still can extend for many hours and even days.<ref>{{Cite web\n| title = Electronic reservation system for border crossings at the Estonia-Russia checkpoints; updates on the waiting lines. | url = https://www.eestipiir.ee/yphis/index.action}}</ref>\n\n{{gallery\n|title =E20 route, west to east\n|File:M62 motorway, Calderdale.jpg|The M62 passes [[Scammonden Reservoir]] in [[West Yorkshire]]\n|File:E20 53.jpg|E&nbsp;20 near [[Odense]], [[Denmark]]\n|File:Copenhagen airport from air.jpg|E20 next to the [[Copenhagen Airport]]\n|File:\u00d6resundsbron i solnedg\u00e5ng 2.jpg|[[Oresund Bridge]], between [[Denmark]] and [[Sweden]]\n|File:\u00d6resundsbrons vajrar 2.jpg|On Oresund Bridge\n|File:Landskrona, 2006-09-11.jpg|East coast of Oresund, between [[Malm\u00f6]] and [[Helsingborg]], showing the city of [[Landskrona]].\n|File:Tallinn-Narva maantee.jpg|Near [[J\u00e4gala]], Estonia\n||Border between [[Narva]] (Estonia) (left) and [[Ivangorod]] (Russia)\n}}\n\n== Itinerary ==\n*{{flag|Ireland}}\n**{{jct|country=IRL|N|18}}: [[Shannon, County Clare|Shannon]] - [[Limerick]]\n**{{jct|country=IRL|M|7}}: [[Limerick]] - [[Borris-in-Ossory]] ({{BAB-E|201|IE}}) - [[Portlaoise]] - [[Naas]]\n**{{jct|country=IRL|N|7}}: [[Naas]] - [[Dublin]]\n**{{jct|country=IRL|M|50}}: [[Dublin]]\n*Gap ([[Irish Sea]])\n**[[File:Ferry Sign.svg|20px|link=Ferry]]: {{flagicon|Ireland}} [[Dublin]] - {{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[Liverpool]]\n*{{flag|United Kingdom}}\n**{{jct|country=GBR|A|5036}}: [[Bootle]]\n**{{jct|country=GBR|M|57}}: '''[[Liverpool]]''' Outer Ring Road (''Whole length'')\n**{{jct|country=GBR|M|62}}: [[Huyton]] - '''[[Manchester]]''' (Interchange with {{BAB-E|5}} and start of multiplex with {{BAB-E|22}} at [[File:UK-Motorway-M6.svg|x15px|link=M6 motorway]] [[Warrington]])\n**{{jct|country=GBR|M|60}}: '''[[Manchester]]''' Outer Ring Road (''Clockwise'')\n**{{jct|country=GBR|M|62}}: '''[[Manchester]]''' - [[File:UK road A63.PNG|40px|link=A63 road]] (Interchange with {{BAB-E|15}} at [[File:UK-Motorway-A1(M).svg|x15px|link=A1(M) motorway]] [[Pontefract]] and end of multiplex with {{BAB-E|22}} at [[File:UK-Motorway-M18.svg|x15px|link=M18 motorway]] [[Goole]])\n**{{jct|country=GBR|A|63}}: [[File:UK-Motorway-M62.svg|x15px|link=M62 motorway]] - [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]]\n**{{jct|country=GBR|A|1033}}: [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]]\n*Gap ([[North Sea]])\n**{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]] - {{flagicon|Denmark}} [[Esbjerg]]\n*{{flag|Denmark}}\n**{{BAB-E|20|DK}}: [[Esbjerg]] - [[Kolding]] ({{BAB-E|45|DK}}) - [[K\u00f8ge]] (Start of Concurrency with {{BAB-E|47|DK}} {{BAB-E|55|DK}}) - [[K\u00f8benhavn]] (End of Concurrency with {{BAB-E|47|DK}} {{BAB-E|55|DK}})\n*{{flag|Sweden}}\n**{{BAB-E|20|S}}: [[Malm\u00f6]] ({{jct|country=SWE|E|22|E|65|rdt=y}}, Start of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|6|rdt=y}}) - [[Helsingborg]] ({{jct|country=SWE|E|4|rdt=y}}) - [[Gothenburg]] ({{jct|country=SWE|E|45|rdt=y}}, End of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|6|rdt=y}}) - [[\u00d6rebro]] (Start of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|18|rdt=y}}) - [[Arboga]] (End of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|18|rdt=y}}) - [[Eskilstuna]] - [[S\u00f6dert\u00e4lje]] (Start of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|4|rdt=y}}) - [[Stockholm]] (End of Concurrency with {{jct|country=SWE|E|4|rdt=y}}, Towards {{jct|country=SWE|E|18|rdt=y}})\n*Gap ([[Baltic Sea]])\n**[[File:Ferry Sign.svg|20px|link=Ferry]]: {{flagicon|Sweden}} [[Stockholm]] - {{flagicon|Estonia}} [[Tallinn]]\n*{{flag|Estonia}}\n**J\u00f5e, Narva maantee, Tartu maantee: [[Tallinn]] ({{BAB-E|67|EE}})\n**{{jct|country=EST|N|1}}: [[Tallinn]] ({{BAB-E|67|EE}} {{BAB-E|263|EE}} {{BAB-E|265|EE}}) - [[J\u00f5hvi]] ({{BAB-E|264|EE}}) - [[Narva]]\n*{{flag|Russia}}\