{"title_page": "Idaho State Highway 28", "text_new": "{{short description|State highway in Idaho, United States}}\n{{Infobox road\n|state=ID\n|type=SH\n|route=28\n|alternate_name=Sacajawea Historic Byway\n|map={{maplink|frame=yes|plain=yes|frame-align=center|frame-width=290|frame-height=310|type=line|raw={{Wikipedia:Map data/Wikipedia KML/Idaho State Highway 28}}}}\n|map_custom=yes\n|map_notes=SH-28 highlighted in red\n|maint=[[Idaho Transportation Department|ITD]]\n|length_mi=135.645\n|length_round=3\n|length_ref=<ref name=\"ITD\">{{cite web|url=http://itd.idaho.gov/highways/milepointlog/mplog/StateHighway28.html|title=Milepost Log for Highway 28|accessdate=2008-05-15|publisher=Idaho Transportation Department|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512104821/http://itd.idaho.gov/highways/milepointlog/mplog/StateHighway28.html|archive-date=2012-05-12|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|direction_a=South\n|terminus_a={{jct|state=ID|SH|33}} west of [[Mud Lake, Idaho|Mud Lake]]\n|junction={{jct|state=ID|SH|29}} in [[Leadore, Idaho|Leadore]]\n\n|direction_b=North\n|terminus_b={{jct|state=ID|US|93}} in [[Salmon, Idaho|Salmon]]\n|previous_type=SH\n|previous_route=27\n|next_type=SH\n|next_route=29\n}}\n\n'''Idaho State Highway 28''' ('''SH-28''') is a {{convert|135.645|mi|km|-long|adj=mid}} [[state highway]] in [[Idaho]] which runs from [[Idaho State Highway 33]] (SH-33) near [[Mud Lake, Idaho|Mud Lake]] to [[U.S. Route 93 in Idaho|U.S. Route 93]] in [[Salmon, Idaho|Salmon]]. The entire length of the route is designated as the '''Sacajawea Historic Byway''' by the state of Idaho.<ref name=\"Byway\">{{cite web |author=[[Idaho Transportation Department]] |publisher=[[America's Byways]] |url=http://www.idahobyways.gov/byways/sacajewea.aspx |title=Sacajawea Scenic Byway |work=Idaho's Scenic Byways |accessdate=January 29, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130430125032/http://www.idahobyways.gov/byways/sacajewea.aspx |archive-date=April 30, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Route description==\n[[File:Lemhi valley shots, Idaho (8124278403).jpg|thumb|left|View along Idaho State Highway in Lemhi Valley, October 2012]]\nIdaho State Highway 28 begins at an intersection with [[Idaho State Highway 33|ID 33]]. The route heads northwest before passing the Mud Lake Airport, proceeding to an intersection with [[Idaho State Highway 22|State Highway 22]].  After a long distance, it proceeds through the Lemhi Valley, bending north before curving northwest again for a short distance. The roadway passes the Leadore Airport on its way into [[Leadore, Idaho|Leadore]], meeting [[Idaho State Highway 29]] while in the community. Just after exiting the town, the road travels parallel to the [[Lemhi River]] for several miles before ending at [[U.S. Route 93 in Idaho|U.S. Route 93]] in the community of [[Salmon, Idaho|Salmon]].<ref name=\"ITD\" />\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n==Major junctions==\n{{jcttop|state=ID|length_ref=<ref name=\"ITD\" />}}\n{{IDint\n | county=Jefferson\n | location=none\n | mile=0.000<!--Starts at MP 15.150-->\n | road={{jct|state=ID|ID|33|city1=Rexburg|city2=Idaho Falls|location3=[[Idaho National Laboratory|INL Site North]]}}\n | notes=Southern terminus; Sacajawea Historic Byway continues on SH-33 east {{convert|15.15|mi|km}} to [[Interstate 15 in Idaho|I-15]]}}\n{{jctco|state=ID|county=Butte}}\n{{IDint\n | county=Clark\n | location=none\n | mile=15.460<!--30.61 - 15.15-->\n | road={{jct|state=ID|ID|22|city1=Arco|city2=Dubois}}\n}}\n{{IDint\n | county=Lemhi\n | cspan=2\n | location=Leadore\n | mile=75.079<!--90.229 - 15.15-->\n | road={{jct|state=ID|ID|29|location1=[[Dillon, Montana|Dillon]]}}\n | notes=Southern terminus of SH-29; former SH-28 north}}\n{{IDint\n | location=Salmon\n | mile=120.495<!--135.645 - 15.15-->\n | road={{jct|state=ID|US|93|location1=[[Hamilton, Montana|Hamilton]]|location2=[[Missoula, Montana|Missoula]]|city3=Challis}}\n | notes=Northern terminus; highway continues as US-93 north (Main Street west)}}\n{{Jctbtm}}\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|U.S. Roads}}\n* [[List of state highways in Idaho]]\n* [[List of highways numbered 28]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|22em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Attached KML|display=inline,title}}\n{{commons category-inline|Idaho State Highway 28}}\n\n\n[[Category:State highways in Idaho|028]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Jefferson County, Idaho]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Butte County, Idaho]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Clark County, Idaho]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Lemhi County, Idaho]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|State highway in Idaho, United States}}\n{{Infobox road\n|state=ID\n|type=SH\n|route=28\n|map={{maplink|frame=yes|plain=yes|frame-align=center|frame-width=290|frame-height=310|type=line|raw={{Wikipedia:Map data/Wikipedia KML/Idaho State Highway 28}}}}\n|map_custom=yes\n|map_notes=SH-28 highlighted in red\n|maint=[[Idaho Transportation Department|ITD]]\n|length_mi=135.645\n|length_round=3\n|length_ref=<ref name=\"ITD\">{{cite web|url=http://itd.idaho.gov/highways/milepointlog/mplog/StateHighway28.html|title=Milepost Log for Highway 28|accessdate=2008-05-15|publisher=Idaho Transportation Department|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512104821/http://itd.idaho.gov/highways/milepointlog/mplog/StateHighway28.html|archive-date=2012-05-12|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|direction_a=\n|starting_terminus=\n|direction_b=\n|ending_terminus=\n|previous_type=SH\n|previous_route=27\n|next_type=SH\n|next_route=29\n}}\n\n'''Idaho State Highway 28''' ('''SH-28''') is a {{convert|135.645|mi|km|-long|adj=mid}} [[state highway]] in [[Idaho]] which runs from [[Salmon, Idaho]] to [[Interstate 15 in Idaho|Interstate 15]] (I-15) near the [[Continental Divide]].\n\nIt runs through [[Tendoy, Idaho]] in [[Lemhi County, Idaho]].\n\n==Route description==\n[[File:Lemhi valley shots, Idaho (8124278403).jpg|thumb|left|View along Idaho State Highway in Lemhi Valley, October 2012]]\nIdaho State Highway 28 begins at an intersection with [[U.S. Route 93 in Idaho|U.S. Route 93]] in the community of [[Salmon, Idaho|Salmon]]. The highway proceeds southeast through the Lemhi Valley, traveling parallel to the [[Lemhi River]] for several miles. The road passes through [[Leadore, Idaho|Leadore]], intersecting [[Idaho State Highway 29]] while in the community. Just after exiting the town, the highway passes the Leadore Airport. The roadway continues southeastward for a short distance before bending south and proceeding through the Lemhi Valley. After a long distance, the route bends back southeastward, proceeding to an intersection with [[Idaho State Highway 22|State Highway 22]]. The route continues southeast before passing the Mud Lake Airport, and intersecting [[Idaho State Highway 33|ID 33]]. The road runs concurrently for several miles, traveling eastward. The highway bends southeast, and reaches its western terminus, an interchange with [[Interstate 15 in Idaho|Interstate 15]].<ref name=\"Googlemaps\">{{Google maps |url=https://maps.google.com/maps?saddr=Main+St&daddr=ID-28+S%2FID-33+E%2FE+1500+N&hl=en&ll=44.425934,-113.076782&spn=2.32624,3.532104&sll=43.831005,-112.195988&sspn=0.004621,0.006899&geocode=FWpJsQIdVDc2-Q%3BFXTOnAId5wNQ-Q&t=h&mra=dme&mrsp=1&sz=17&z=8 |title=Overview Map of Idaho State Highway 28 |accessdate=January 29, 2013}}</ref> The entire length of the route is designated as the Sacajawea Historic Byway by the state of Idaho.<ref name=\"Byway\">{{cite web |author=[[Idaho Transportation Department]] |publisher=[[America's Byways]] |url=http://www.idahobyways.gov/byways/sacajewea.aspx |title=Sacajawea Scenic Byway |work=Idaho's Scenic Byways |accessdate=January 29, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130430125032/http://www.idahobyways.gov/byways/sacajewea.aspx |archive-date=April 30, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n{{-}}\n\n==Major junctions==\n{{jcttop|state=ID|length_ref=<ref name=\"ITD\"/>}}\n{{IDint\n | county=Jefferson\n | cspan=4\n | location=none\n | type=concur\n | mile=0.000\n | road={{jct|state=ID|I|15|ID|33}}\n | notes=Eastern terminus; eastern end of SH-33 concurrency}}\n{{IDint\n | location=none\n | type=concur\n | mile=15.150\n | road={{jct|state=ID|ID|33}}\n | notes=Western terminus of SH-33 concurrency}}\n{{IDint\n | location=none\n | mile=15.212\n | road=ID-28 Connector\n | notes=Northern terminus of SH-28 Connector}}\n{{IDint\n | location=none\n | mile=17.700\n | road=Monteview Highway\n | notes=}}\n{{IDint\n | county=Clark\n | location=none\n | mile=30.610\n | road={{jct|state=ID|ID|22}}\n | notes=}}\n{{IDint\n | county=Lemhi\n | cspan=3\n | location=Leadore\n | mile=90.229\n | road={{jct|state=ID|ID|29}}\n | notes=Western terminus of SH-29}}\n{{IDint\n | location=Tendoy\n | mile=115.734\n | road=Lewis and Clark Back Country Scenic Byway\n | notes=Western terminus of the byway}}\n{{IDint\n | location=Salmon\n | mile=135.645\n | road={{jct|state=ID|US|93|name1=Challis Street}}\n | notes=Western terminus}}\n{{Jctbtm|keys=concur}}\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|U.S. Roads}}\n* [[List of state highways in Idaho]]\n* [[List of highways numbered 28]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|22em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Attached KML|display=inline,title}}\n{{commons category-inline|Idaho State Highway 28}}\n\n\n[[Category:State highways in Idaho|028]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Jefferson County, Idaho]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Clark County, Idaho]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Lemhi County, Idaho]]\n", "name_user": "Greggens", "label": "safe", "comment": "corrected info", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idaho_State_Highway_28"}
