{"title_page": "Katie Sheridan", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Katie Sheridan\n| image        = Katie Sheridan 142 final cropped smallrrr-1.jpg\n| caption      = Sheridan in 2011\n| birth_name   = Katie Teresa Sheridan\n| birth_place  = [[London]], [[England]]\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1986|12|29}}\n| occupation   = [[Actress]]\n| years_active = 1998\u2013present\n| awards       = \n}}\n\n'''Katie Teresa Sheridan''' is an English actress. She has appeared in feature films such as ''[[Heretiks]]'' (2018) and ''Together'' (2018), and her Television roles include appearances in the BBC series [[Doctors (2000 TV series)|''Doctors'']], ''[[Waking the Dead (TV series)|Waking the Dead]]'' and ''[[Love Soup]]''. Sheridan first became known for her role as Sophie Norton in the Nickelodeon comedy series ''[[Genie in the House]]''.  In 2015 Sheridan created and starred in her own online series, romantic comedy ''[[Match Not Found]]''. She was nominated for Best Lead Actor in a web series at the [[Raindance Film Festival]] 2016 for this role.\n\n==Personal life==\n\nSheridan attended East Berkshire College and Middlesex University. During an appearance on Reel Geek Girls, she talks about her love for [[Game of Thrones]] and [[Harry Potter]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Katie Sheridan Interview - Reel Geek Girls #18 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UxlnVJ0Ov5E |website=Drew's Corner on YouTube |accessdate=3 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nKatie Sheridan made her first television appearance in ITV's real crime series ''Cracking the Killer's Code'', and appeared in a number of BBC productions including ''[[Powers (UK TV series)|Powers]]'', ''[[Waking the Dead (TV series)|Waking the Dead]]'', ''In2minds'', ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]'', ''[[Love Soup]]'', ''If...TV Goes Down The Tube'' and ''[[Brief Encounters (TV series)|Brief Encounters]]''. She also played young Grace in the feature film ''[[Lighthouse Hill (film)|Lighthouse Hill]]''.\n\nSheridan gained a following for her role as Sophie Norton in the Nickelodeon comedy series ''[[Genie in the House]]''. The show ran for three seasons, with a total of 78 episodes and was shown in over 100 countries. As of March 2012 ''[[Genie in the House]]'' was aired in the US on the Starz Kids & Family cable network.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.starz.com/series/genieinthehouse |title=Genie in the House on Starz |publisher=Starz |accessdate=2013-03-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130515193101/http://www.starz.com/series/GenieintheHouse |archivedate=15 May 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nSheridan has appeared in a number of adverts including the 2015 advert for [[Oral-B]] toothbrushes and [[Virgin Trains]]' \"Bound for Glory\" campaign.<ref>[https://www.virgintrains.co.uk/our-blog/news/2015/09/bound-for-glory Bound for Glory]</ref> Sheridan also appeared in the ''[[Thorntons]]'' Christmas and Easter adverts.\n\nSheridan created, co-wrote and co-produced the online series ''[[Match Not Found]]''<ref>https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCEQzHBwF4ojRPiuMx1UpioA/featured</ref> with British playwright [[Alex Oates]]. A romantic comedy, Sheridan plays the luckless in love Kat as the series follows her eventful quest for the right man. She was nominated for Best Lead Actor in a web series at the Raindance Film Festival 2016<ref>http://raindancefestival.org/programme-2016/</ref> for this role, along with the show being screened as part of the festival's Official Selection. ''Match Not Found'' was also announced as a finalist in the C21 International Drama Awards for \"Best Digital Original Drama\",<ref>https://www.c21media.net/finalists-named-in-c21-drama-awards/</ref> and has had over two million views on YouTube.\n\nSheridan portrays Sister Margaret in Paul Hyett's horror film ''[[Heretiks]]'', which is set in a priory during the 17th century and was filmed on location in Wales.<ref>http://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/exclusive-image-paul-hyett-horror-heretiks/</ref> In 2018 Sheridan also played social worker Carol in Together, written and directed by [[Paul Duddridge]], starring [[Peter Bowles]] and [[Sylvia Syms]]. Sheridan appears in [[Melanie Martinez (singer)|Melanie Martinez]]'s musical horror fantasy film ''K-12''.\n\n==Filmography==\n{|class=wikitable\n!Year !!Film/TV series !!Role  !!Production\n\n|-\n|2019\n|''K-12''\n|Lorelai\n|[[Atlantic Records]]\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Heretiks]]''\n|Sister Margaret || Sterling Pictures Ltd\n|-\n|2018 ||''Together'' || Carol Turner || Siempre Viva Productions / Colour TV\n|-\n|2018\n|Rebecca Gold\n|Agent Nine ||  Web Series\n|-\n|2016\n|[[Doctors (2000 TV series)|Doctors]]\n|Ellie Richards || BBC Television \n|-\n|2015 - 2017 \n|''[[Match Not Found]]''\n|Kat || Bytesized Entertainment\n|-\n|2014 ||''[[The Confusion of Tongues]]'' ||Harriet || Grand Independent\n|-\n|2014 ||''50 Kisses'' ||Mary || Guerilla Films\n|-\n|2014 ||''Hi-Lo Joe'' ||Cassie || Sonder Films\n|-\n|2013 ||''Which Is Witch'' ||Kelly || I Love Television\n|-\n|2012 ||''Crushing Snails'' ||Sarah || Grand Independent\n|-\n|2006-2010 ||''[[Genie in the House]]'' ||Sophie Norton || Nickelodeon\n|-\n|2006 ||''[[Brief Encounters (TV series)|Brief Encounters]]'' ||Rachel Graham || BBC Television\n|-\n|2005 ||''[[Love Soup]]'' ||Teenage Girl || BBC Television\n|-\n|2005 ||''If...(Television Went Down The Tube) '' || Lizzie || BBC Television\n|-\n|2004 ||''In2Minds '' ||Becky || BBC Television\n|-\n|2004 ||''[[Waking the Dead (TV series)|Waking the Dead]]'' ||Sarah || BBC Television\n|-\n|2004 ||''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]'' ||Becky Eastwood || BBC Television\n|-\n|2004 ||''[[Powers (UK TV series)|Powers]]'' ||Sam Ryan || CBBC Television\n|-\n|2004 ||''[[Lighthouse Hill (film)|Lighthouse Hill]]'' ||Young Grace || Carnaby Films\n|-\n|2003 ||'' Cracking The Killers Code'' ||Linda || Granada Television\n|}\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External 