{"title_page": "Sinibotys butleri", "text_new": "{{Italic title}}\n{{Taxobox\n| image = \n| image_caption =\n| regnum = [[Animal]]ia\n| phylum = [[Arthropod]]a\n| classis = [[Insect]]a\n| ordo = [[Lepidoptera]]\n| familia = [[Crambidae]]\n| subfamilia = [[Pyraustinae]]\n| genus = ''[[Sinibotys]]''\n| species = '''''S. butleri'''''\n| binomial = ''Sinibotys butleri''\n| binomial_authority = (South in Leech & South, 1901)<ref name=GlobIZ>{{cite web |website=www.pyraloidea.org |url=http://globiz.pyraloidea.org/Pages/Reports/TaxonReport.aspx?ReturnUrl=%2fPages%2fReports%2fTaxonomyReport.aspx%3fAspxAutoDetectCookieSupport%3d1&AspxAutoDetectCookieSupport=1 |title=Global Information System on Pyraloidea (GlobIZ) |last1=Nuss |first1=Matthias |last2=Landry |first2=Bernard |last3=Mally |first3=Richard |last4=Vegliante |first4=Francesca |last5=Tr\u00e4nkner |first5=Andreas |last6=Bauer |first6=Franziska |last7=Hayden |first7=James |last8=Segerer |first8=Andreas |last9=Schouten |first9=Rob |last10=Li |first10=Houhun |last11=Trofimova |first11=Tatiana |last12=Solis |first12=M. Alma |author-link12=Maria Alma Solis |last13=De Prins |first13=Jurate |last14=Speidel |first14=Wolfgang |date=2003\u20132020 |access-date=2020-04-18 |language=English }}</ref>\n| synonyms = \n*''Crocidophora butleri'' <small>South in Leech & South, 1901</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Sinibotys butleri''''' is a [[Pyraloidea|snout moth]] in the [[subfamily]] [[Pyraustinae]] in the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Crambidae]]. It was described in the genus ''[[Crocidophora]]'' by [[Richard South]] in 1901 based on a single female [[imago]] collected in [[Ningbo]] in [[China]]'s [[Zhejiang]] province.<ref name=Leech-South-1901>{{cite journal |last1=Leech |first1=John Henry |author1-link=John Henry Leech |last2=South |first2=Richard |author2-link=Richard South |date=1901 |title=Lepidoptera Heterocera from China, Japan, and Corea. Part V |journal=Transactions of the Entomological Society of London |volume=1901 |pages=385-514, pls 14-15 |url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/130127#page/423/mode/1up }}</ref>{{rp|480}} The species is [[sexual dimorphism|sexually dimorphic]], with females exhibiting shorter, less pointed forewings than the males. The [[imago|imagines]] and genitalia of the species are illustrated in Lee et al. (2018).<ref name=Lee-eal-2018>{{cite journal |last1=Lee |first1=Tak\u2013Gi |last2=Ko |first2=Jae\u2013Ho |last3=Lee |first3=Dong\u2013June |last4=Kim |first4=Hyeong\u2013Kyu |last5=Cha |first5=Yeong\u2013Bin |last6=Bayarsaikhan |first6=Ulziijargal |last7=Na |first7=Sol\u2013Moon |last8=Shin |first8=Young\u2013Min |last9=Park |first9=Bo\u2013Sun |last10=Bae |first10=Yang\u2013Seop |date=2018 |title=Two species of Pyraustine moths new to Korea (Lepidoptera: Crambidae) |journal=Journal of Asia-Pacific Biodiversity |volume=12 |issue=1 |pages=79-82 |issn=2287-884X |doi=10.1016/j.japb.2018.09.010 |url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2287884X18303315/pdfft?md5=4180a7e3c2a06be97071d1c3733184b8&pid=1-s2.0-S2287884X18303315-main.pdf }}</ref>\n\n==Biology==\nThe [[caterpillar]]s feed on leaves of the [[bamboo]] species ''[[Phyllostachys edulis]]'' and ''[[Phyllostachys nigra|P. nigra]]'' forma ''henonis'' in Japan.<ref name=Yamanaka-Sasaki-2013>{{cite book |last1=Yamanaka |first1=Hiroshi |last2=Sasaki |first2=A. |date=2013 |chapter=Pyraustinae |editor1-last=Nasu |editor1-first=Y. |editor2-last=Hirowatari |editor2-first=T. |editor3-last=Kishida |editor3-first=Y. |title=The standard of moths in Japan IV |publisher=Gakken Education Publishing |place=Tokyo |pages=415-478, pl 4 figs 51-69 |isbn=9784054051102 }}</ref>\n\n==Distribution==\nThe species was originally described from [[China]],<ref name=Leech-South-1901/> and was later also recorded from [[Japan]], specifically from [[Honshu]].<ref name=Yamanaka-2007>{{cite journal |last=Yamanaka |first=Hiroshi |date=2007 |title=An unrecorded species of Pyraustinae (Pyralidae) from Japan |journal=Japan Heterocerists' Journal |place=Tokyo |volume=245 |pages=355-356 }}</ref><ref name=Mano-2009>{{cite journal |last=Mano |first=Takahiro |date=2009 |title=Record of ''Sinibotys butleri'' (South) (Crambidae) from Nagoya City, Aichi Prefecture, Honshu, Japan |journal=Yugato |volume=197 |pages=116 |language=ja }}</ref> Lee et al. (2018) reported the species for the first time from [[Korea]].<ref name=Lee-eal-2018/>\n\nThe species was apparently transported via [[larva]]e to a large-scale garden centre in [[Spain]], from where it spread further over [[Europe]].<ref name=Lepiforum>{{cite web |last=Rodeland |first=J\u00fcrgen |title=''Sinibotys butleri'' (SOUTH, 1901) - Bambusz\u00fcnsler |website=Lepiforum |url=http://www.lepiforum.de/lepiwiki.pl?Sinibotys_Butleri |access-date=2020-04-18 |language=de }}</ref> Caterpillars were subsequently reported from [[Belgium]] in 2013 and 2015,<ref name=vanderStraten-2014>{{cite journal |last=van der Straten |first=Marja |date=2014 |title=Faunistische mededelingen |journal=Franje |volume=34 |pages=40-42 |issn=1388-4409 |url=https://www.sectieterhaar.com/Franjes/FRANJE%2034%20Najaar%202014.pdf |language=nl }}</ref>{{rp|40-41}}<ref name=dePrins-eal-2015>{{cite journal |last1=De Prins |first1=Willy |last2=Steemanen |first2=Chris |last3=Sierens |first3=Tom |date=2015 |title=Interessante waarnemingen van Lepidoptera in Belgi\u00eb in 2014 (Lepidoptera) |journal=Phegea |volume=43 |issue=4 |pages=98-103 |issn=0771-5277 |url=http://www.phegea.org/Phegea/2015/Phegea43-4_98-103.pdf |language=nl }}</ref> from the [[Netherlands]] in 2014,<ref>{{cite web |title=Exotische soorten |website=microlepidoptera.nl - Atlas van de kleinere vlinders in Nederland |url=http://www.microvlinders.nl/library/exotenenadventieven.php |access-date=2020-04-18 |language=nl }}</ref> and from [[France]] in 2015,<ref name=Rogard-2015>{{cite journal |last=Rogard |first=Jacques |date=2015 |title=Premi\u00e8re signalisation en France de ''Sinibotys butleri'' (Leech & South, 1901) (Lep. Crambidae, Pyraustinae) |journal=Oreina |volume=32 |pages=7 |language=fr }}</ref> where it is now recorded from the [[Departments of France|departments]] of [[Gironde]], [[Landes (department)|Landes]] and [[Pyr\u00e9n\u00e9es-Atlantiques]].<ref>{{cite web |title=''Sinibotys butleri'' (Leech & South, 1901)\t|website=Oreina - Les Papillons de France |url=https://oreina.org/artemisiae/observatoire/index.php?module=fiche&action=fiche&d=hetero&id=813856 |access-date=2020-04-18 |language=fr }}</ref> The first [[Germany|German]] record is from June 2018 from [[Munich]].<ref name=Morawietz-2019>{{cite journal |last=Morawietz |first=Benjamin |date=2019 |title=Erster Nachweis des Z\u00fcnslers ''Circobotys butleri'' (SOUTH, 1901) in Deutschland. Diskussion einer m\u00f6glichen Etablierung in Belgien und Europa (Lepidoptera: Crambidae) |journal=Nachrichtenblatt der bayerischen Entomologen |volume=68 |issue=1/2 |pages=41-46 |language=de }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q20720154}}\n\n[[Category:Moths described in 1901]]\n[[Category:Pyraustinae]]\n\n\n{{Pyraustinae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Italic title}}\n{{Taxobox\n| image = \n| image_caption =\n| regnum = [[Animal]]ia\n| phylum = [[Arthropod]]a\n| classis = [[Insect]]a\n| ordo = [[Lepidoptera]]\n| familia = [[Crambidae]]\n| subfamilia = [[Pyraustinae]]\n| genus = ''[[Sinibotys]]''\n| species = '''''S. butleri'''''\n| binomial = ''Sinibotys butleri''\n| binomial_authority = (South in Leech & South, 1901)<ref name=GlobIZ>{{cite web |website=www.pyraloidea.org |url=http://globiz.pyraloidea.org/Pages/Reports/TaxonReport.aspx?ReturnUrl=%2fPages%2fReports%2fTaxonomyReport.aspx%3fAspxAutoDetectCookieSupport%3d1&AspxAutoDetectCookieSupport=1 |title=Global Information System on Pyraloidea (GlobIZ) |last1=Nuss |first1=Matthias |last2=Landry |first2=Bernard |last3=Mally |first3=Richard |last4=Vegliante |first4=Francesca |last5=Tr\u00e4nkner |first5=Andreas |last6=Bauer |first6=Franziska |last7=Hayden |first7=James |last8=Segerer |first8=Andreas |last9=Schouten |first9=Rob |last10=Li |first10=Houhun |last11=Trofimova |first11=Tatiana |last12=Solis |first12=M. Alma |author-link12=Maria Alma Solis |last13=De Prins |first13=Jurate |last14=Speidel |first14=Wolfgang |date=2003\u20132020 |access-date=2020-04-18 |language=English }}</ref>\n| synonyms = \n*''Crocidophora butleri'' <small>South in Leech & South, 1901</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Sinibotys butleri''''' is a [[Pyraloidea|snout moth]] in the [[subfamily]] [[Pyraustinae]] in the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Crambidae]]. It was described in the genus ''[[Crocidophora]]'' by [[Richard South]] in 1901 based on a single female [[imago]] collected in [[Ningbo]] in [[China]]'s [[Zhejiang]] province.<ref name=Leech-South-1901>{{cite journal |last1=Leech |first1=John Henry |author1-link=John Henry Leech |last2=South |first2=Richard |author2-link=Richard South |date=1901 |title=Lepidoptera Heterocera from China, Japan, and Corea. Part V |journal=Transactions of the Entomological Society of London |volume=1901 |pages=385-514, pls 14-15 |url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/130127#page/423/mode/1up }}</ref>{{rp|480}} The species is [[sexual dimorphism|sexually dimorphic]], with females exhibiting shorter, less pointed forewings than the males. The [[imago|imagines]] and genitalia of the species are illustrated in Lee et al. (2018).<ref name=Lee-eal-2018>{{cite journal |last1=Lee |first1=Tak\u2013Gi |last2=Ko |first2=Jae\u2013Ho |last3=Lee |first3=Dong\u2013June |last4=Kim |first4=Hyeong\u2013Kyu |last5=Cha |first5=Yeong\u2013Bin |last6=Bayarsaikhan |first6=Ulziijargal |last7=Na |first7=Sol\u2013Moon |last8=Shin |first8=Young\u2013Min |last9=Park |first9=Bo\u2013Sun |last10=Bae |first10=Yang\u2013Seop |date=2018 |title=Two species of Pyraustine moths new to Korea (Lepidoptera: Crambidae) |journal=Journal of Asia-Pacific Biodiversity |volume=12 |issue=1 |pages=79-82 |issn=2287-884X |doi=10.1016/j.japb.2018.09.010 |url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2287884X18303315/pdfft?md5=4180a7e3c2a06be97071d1c3733184b8&pid=1-s2.0-S2287884X18303315-main.pdf }}</ref>\n\n==Biology==\nThe [[caterpillar]]s feed on leaves of the [[bamboo]] species ''[[Phyllostachys edulis]]'' and ''[[Phyllostachys nigra|P. nigra]]'' forma ''henonis'' in Japan.<ref name=Yamanaka-Sasaki-2013>{{cite book |last1=Yamanaka |first1=Hiroshi |last2=Sasaki |first2=A. |date=2013 |chapter=Pyraustinae |editor1-last=Nasu |editor1-first=Y. |editor2-last=Hirowatari |editor2-first=T. |editor3-last=Kishida |editor3-first=Y. |title=The standard of moths in Japan IV |publisher=Gakken Education Publishing |place=Tokyo |pages=415-478, pl 4 figs 51-69 |isbn=9784054051102 }}</ref>\n\n==Distribution==\nThe species was originally described from [[China]],<ref name=Leech-South-1901/> and was later also recorded from [[Japan]], specifically from [[Honshu]].<ref name=Yamanaka-2007>{{cite journal |last=Yamanaka |first=Hiroshi |date=2007 |title=An unrecorded species of Pyraustinae (Pyralidae) from Japan |journal=Japan Heterocerists' Journal |place=Tokyo |volume=245 |pages=355-356 }}</ref><ref name=Mano-2009>{{cite journal |last=Mano |first=Takahiro |date=2009 |title=Record of ''Sinibotys butleri'' (South) (Crambidae) from Nagoya City, Aichi Prefecture, Honshu, Japan |journal=Yugato |volume=197 |pages=116 |language=ja }}</ref> Lee et al. (2018) reported the species for the first time from [[Korea]].<ref name=Lee-eal-2018/>\n\nThe species was apparently transported via [[larva]]e to a large-scale garden centre in [[Spain]], from where it spread further over [[Europe]].<ref name=Lepiforum>{{cite web |last=Rodeland |first=J\u00fcrgen |title=''Sinibotys butleri'' (SOUTH, 1901) - Bambusz\u00fcnsler |website=Lepiforum |url=http://www.lepiforum.de/lepiwiki.pl?Sinibotys_Butleri |access-date=2020-04-18 |language=de }}</ref> Caterpillars were subsequently reported from [[Belgium]] in 2013 and 2015,<ref name=vanderStraten-2014>{{cite journal |last=van der Straten |first=Marja |date=2014 |title=Faunistische mededelingen |journal=Franje |volume=34 |pages=40-42 |issn=1388-4409 |url=https://www.sectieterhaar.com/Franjes/FRANJE%2034%20Najaar%202014.pdf |language=nl }}</ref>{{rp|40-41}}<ref name=dePrins-eal-2015>{{cite journal |last1=De Prins |first1=Willy |last2=Steemanen |first2=Chris |last3=Sierens |first3=Tom |date=2015 |title=Interessante waarnemingen van Lepidoptera in Belgi\u00eb in 2014 (Lepidoptera) |journal=Phegea |volume=43 |issue=4 |pages=98-103 |issn=0771-5277 |url=http://www.phegea.org/Phegea/2015/Phegea43-4_98-103.pdf |language=nl }}</ref> from the [[Netherlands]] in 2014,<ref>{{cite web |title=Exotische soorten |website=microlepidoptera.nl - Atlas van de kleinere vlinders in Nederland |url=http://www.microvlinders.nl/library/exotenenadventieven.php |access-date=2020-04-18 |language=nl }}</ref> and from [[France]] in 2015,<ref name=Rogard-2015>{{cite journal |last=Rogard |first=Jacques |date=2015 |title=Premi\u00e8re signalisation en France de ''Sinibotys butleri'' (Leech & South, 1901) (Lep. Crambidae, Pyraustinae) |journal=Oreina |volume=32 |pages=7 |language=fr }}</ref> where it is now recorded from the [[Departments of France|departments]] of [[Gironde]], [[Landes]] and [[Pyr\u00e9n\u00e9es-Atlantiques]].<ref>{{cite web |title=''Sinibotys butleri'' (Leech & South, 1901)\t|website=Oreina - Les Papillons de France |url=https://oreina.org/artemisiae/observatoire/index.php?module=fiche&action=fiche&d=hetero&id=813856 |access-date=2020-04-18 |language=fr }}</ref> The first [[Germany|German]] record is from June 2018 from [[Munich]].<ref name=Morawietz-2019>{{cite journal |last=Morawietz |first=Benjamin |date=2019 |title=Erster Nachweis des Z\u00fcnslers ''Circobotys butleri'' (SOUTH, 1901) in Deutschland. Diskussion einer m\u00f6glichen Etablierung in Belgien und Europa (Lepidoptera: Crambidae) |journal=Nachrichtenblatt der bayerischen Entomologen |volume=68 |issue=1/2 |pages=41-46 |language=de }}<