{"title_page": "Black Linn of Blairvaich", "text_new": "#redirect[[List of waterfalls of Scotland]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox waterfall\n| name = Black Linn of Blairvaich\n| photo = A Waterfall on Duchray Water - geograph.org.uk - 1058270.jpg\n| photo_width =\n| photo_caption = \n| map            = Scotland |relief=1\n| coordinates = {{coord|56.16450|-4.49375|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline,title}}\n| location = [[Aberfoyle, Scotland|Aberfoyle]], [[Stirling (council area)|Stirling]], [[Scotland]]\n| type =\n| elevation =\n| height = \n| height_longest =\n| number_drops = \n| width =\n| average_width =\n| watercourse = [[Duchray Water]]\n| average_flow =\n| world_rank =\n}}\n'''Black Linn of Blairvaich''' is a waterfall on the [[Duchray Water]], in the [[Stirling (council area)|Stirling council area]] of [[Scotland]]. It is in Loch Ard Forest, 7&nbsp;km west of [[Aberfoyle, Scotland|Aberfoyle]].<ref>Ordnance Survey 1:25,000 scale Explorer map series, sheets 309-470</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Waterfalls of Scotland]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Waterfalls of Stirling (council area)]]\n\n\n{{Scotland-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Reywas92", "label": "safe", "comment": "no non-map sources for minor feature to passWP:GEOLAND4;WP:NOPAGE", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Black_Linn_of_Blairvaich&redirect=no"}
{"title_page": "Eulimella lissa", "text_new": "{{Italic title}}\n{{Taxobox\n| name = ''Eulimella lissa''\n| image = Eulimella lissa 001.png\n| image_caption = Drawing of a [[gastropod shell|shell]] of ''Eulimella lissa''\n| regnum = [[Animal]]ia\n| phylum = [[Mollusca]]\n| classis = [[Gastropoda]]\n| unranked_superfamilia = clade [[Heterobranchia]]<br/>clade [[Euthyneura]]<br/>clade [[Panpulmonata]]\n| superfamilia = [[Pyramidelloidea]]\n| familia = [[Pyramidellidae]]\n| subfamilia = \n| genus = ''[[Eulimella]]''\n| subgenus = \n| species = '''''E.&nbsp;lissa'''''\n| binomial = ''Eulimella lissa''\n| binomial_authority = A. E. Verrill, 1884\n| synonyms_ref = <ref name=\"WoRMS\" />\n| synonyms = \n* ''Pyramidella lissa'' <small>(A. E. Verrill, 1884)</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Eulimella lissa''''' is a [[species]] of [[sea snail]], a [[marine (ocean)|marine]] [[gastropod]] [[mollusk]] in the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Pyramidellidae]], the pyrams and their allies.<ref name=\"WoRMS\">Rosenberg, G. (2011). ''Eulimella lissa'' A. E. Verrill, 1884. Accessed through:  [[World Register of Marine Species]] at http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=467504 on 2011-10-26</ref><ref>Malacolog - Western atlantic gastropod database.</ref>\n\n==Description==\nThe white shell is small with a length of 6&nbsp;mm. It has a pupiform shape. The [[teleoconch]] contains eight flattened [[Whorl (mollusc)|whorl]]s . The [[Sculpture (mollusc)|sculpture]] is smooth and polished. The [[Suture (anatomy)|suture]] is distinct.<ref>[https://archive.org/stream/manualconch08tryorich#page/n5/mode/2up [[G.W. Tryon]], Manual of Conchology vol. VIII p. 343; 1889]</ref>\n\n==Distribution==\nThis species occurs in the following locations:<ref name=\"WoRMS\" />\n* North West Atlantic\n* [[Cape Hatteras]], North Carolina, USA\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/name/Eulimella+lissa To Biodiversity Heritage Library (8 publications)]\n* [http://www.eol.org/pages/4812285 To Encyclopedia of Life]\n* [http://collections.mnh.si.edu/search/iz/?qn=Eulimella+lissa To USNM Invertebrate Zoology Mollusca Collection]\n* [http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=467504 To World Register of Marine Species]\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5409337}}\n\n[[Category:Eulimella|lissa]]\n[[Category:Gastropods described in 1884]]\n", "text_old": "{{Italic title}}\n{{Taxobox\n| name = ''Eulimella lissa''\n| image = Eulimella lissa 001.png\n| image_caption = Drawing of a [[gastropod shell|shell]] of ''Eulimella lissa''\n| regnum = [[Animal]]ia\n| phylum = [[Mollusca]]\n| classis = [[Gastropoda]]\n| unranked_superfamilia = clade [[Heterobranchia]]<br/>clade [[Euthyneura]]<br/>clade [[Panpulmonata]]\n| superfamilia = [[Pyramidelloidea]]\n| familia = [[Pyramidellidae]]\n| subfamilia = \n| genus = ''[[Eulimella]]''\n| subgenus = \n| species = '''''E.&nbsp;lissa'''''\n| binomial = ''Eulimella lissa''\n| binomial_authority = A. E. Verrill, 1884\n| synonyms_ref = <ref name=\"WoRMS\" />\n| synonyms = \n* ''Pyramidella lissa'' <small>(A. E. Verrill, 1884)</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Eulimella lissa''''' is a [[species]] of [[sea snail]], a [[marine (ocean)|marine]] [[gastropod]] [[mollusk]] in the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Pyramidellidae]], the pyrams and their allies.<ref name=\"WoRMS\">Rosenberg, G. (2011). ''Eulimella lissa'' A. E. Verrill, 1884. Accessed through:  [[World Register of Marine Species]] at http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=467504 on 2011-10-26</ref><ref>Malacolog - Western atlantic gastropod database.</ref>\n\n==Description==\nThe white shell is small with a length of 6&nbsp;mm. It has a pupiform shape. The [[teleoconch]] contains eight flattened [[Whorl (mollusc)|whorl]]s . The [[Sculpture (mollusc)|sculpture]] is smooth and polished. The [[Suture (anatomy)|suture]] is dsitnct.<ref>[https://archive.org/stream/manualconch08tryorich#page/n5/mode/2up [[G.W. Tryon]], Manual of Conchology vol. VIII p. 343; 1889]</ref>\n\n==Distribution==\nThis species occurs in the following locations:<ref name=\"WoRMS\" />\n* North West Atlantic\n* [[Cape Hatteras]], North Carolina, USA\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/name/Eulimella+lissa To Biodiversity Heritage Library (8 publications)]\n* [http://www.eol.org/pages/4812285 To Encyclopedia of Life]\n* [http://collections.mnh.si.edu/search/iz/?qn=Eulimella+lissa To USNM Invertebrate Zoology Mollusca Collection]\n* [http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=467504 To World Register of Marine Species]\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5409337}}\n\n[[Category:Eulimella|lissa]]\n[[Category:Gastropods described in 1884]]\n", "name_user": "Strickesel", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixed spelling found byWikipedia:Typo Team/moss\u2013 you can help!", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eulimella_lissa"}
{"title_page": "Nusraat Faria", "text_new": "{{short description|Bangladeshi film actress, model, television presenter and radio jockey .}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Nusrat Faria\n| image              = Nusrat Faria003.jpg\n| caption            = In 2017\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1995|09|08}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/pg/nusraatfariaofficial/about/?ref=page_internal |title=Nusraat Faria - About |website=Facebook}}</ref>\n| nationality        = [[Bangladesh]]\n| education          = [[Bachelor of Laws]] ([[LLB]])\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* Actress\n* television presenter\n* radio jockey\n* singer\n}}\n| years_active       = 2013\u2013present\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed = yes\n| background = solo_singer\n| genre = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| label = {{flatlist| \n* [[SVF Entertainment|SVF Music]]\n* CMV }}\n}}\n}}\n'''Nusrat Faria''' ({{IPA-hns|nusr\u028ct \u02c8f\u028cr\u026a\u0259|pron}}; born 1985)<ref name=nervous /> is a Bangladeshi film actress, model, pornsta,   television presenter and [[radio jockey]].\n\n==Early life==\nFaria had planned to be an army officer, before she became an actress.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news |last=Chaity |first=Afrose Jahan |date=4 June 2014 |title=Big screen is the place to be' |url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2014/06/03/big-screen-is-the-place-to-be |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune |access-date=13 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nFaria has started her career as a debater participating in a [[Bangladesh Television|BTV]] debate show. She is a national debate  champions in 2010 and 2011. She started her career in show business as a model in several television commercials. Throughout her career, she has worked in various [[television commercials]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://thedailynewnation.com/news/13901/nusrat-faria-in-new-tvcs.html |title=Nusrat Faria in new TVCs |date=2 June 2014 |access-date=28 May 2015 |newspaper=The New Nation}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Nusrat Faria endorsing for commercials |url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2014/12/20/nusrat-faria-endorsing-for-commercials |date=21 December 2014 |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune |access-date=28 May 2015}}</ref> and [[radio programs]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/tv/faguner-bhalobasha-channel-i-1933 |title=Faguner Bhalobasha on Channel i |date=13 February 2015 |access-date=13 May 2015 |newspaper=The Daily Star|publisher=Transcom Group }}</ref> In 2014, she hosted a reality show, ''Fair and Handsome: The Ultimate Man''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.priyo.com/2014/07/21/faria-naval-base-114749.html |title=Faria at the Naval Base |website=priyo.com |type=Blog |access-date=13 May 2015}}</ref>\nShe signed with [[Jaaz Multimedia]] to appear in two films, titled ''[[Aashiqui (2015 film)|Aashiqui]]'' and ''[[Hero 420]]''.<ref name=\":0\" /> The former, being her debut film, released in late 2015<ref>{{Cite news |title=Nusraat Faria\u2019s first hit on the movie screen |url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2015/08/15/nusraat-farias-first-hit-on-the-movie-screen |work=Dhaka Tribune |date=16 August 2015 |access-date=18 July 2017}}</ref> while the latter released in early 2016. The former also earned Faria a [[Meril Prothom Alo Awards|Meril Prothom Alo Award]] for Best Newcomer in film or television.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news |url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/news/103105/Meril-Prothom-Alo-Award-2015-conferred |title=Meril-Prothom Alo Award-2015 conferred |work=Prothom Alo |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> Both films were [[Indo-Bangla joint production|Indo-Bangladeshi joint ventures]], being co-produced by [[Eskay Movies]].\n\nIn 2016, Nusrat also starred in another Indo-Bangladeshi co-production, ''[[Badsha - The Don]]'', directed by [[Baba Yadav]]. The film also starred popular Indian actor [[Jeet (actor)|Jeet]], and is considered a turning point in Faria's career,<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news |url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/news/111647/%E2%80%98Badsha-turning-point-of-my-career%E2%80%99-Nusrat-Faria |title=\u2018Badsha', turning point of my career: Nusrat Faria |work=Prothom Alo |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> earning Faria a [[Tele Cine Awards|Tele Cine Award]] for Best Actress from Bangladesh.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/showtime/2017/05/26/razzak-conferred-lifetime-achievement-award-kolkata/ |title=Razzak conferred with a lifetime achievement award in Kolkata |work=Dhaka Tribune  |access-date=18 July 2017}}</ref>\n[[File:Nusrat Faria Mazhar.jpg|thumb|Faria hosting the grand finale of Parachute Advanced Beliphool Stylish Hair of the Campus 2014, at the [[Radisson Blu]], Dhaka Water Garden, [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh ]]]]\nAfter starring Indo-Bangladeshi films for the past two years, Faria then starred in two Bangladeshi films in 2017, ''Premi o Premi''<ref name=\":2\" /> and ''[[Dhat Teri Ki]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/showbiz/deshi-grapevine/nusrat-farias-new-mission-1351975 |title=Nusrat Faria's New Mission |date=28 January 2017 |work=The Daily Star |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> Faria also recorded dialogue for ''[[Detective (2017 film)|Detective]],'' Bangladesh's first animated film. All three of these films were produced by [[Jaaz Multimedia]] and also starred [[Arifin Shuvo]].\n\n2017 also saw Faria return with the team behind ''Badsha - The Don'' for the film ''[[Boss 2: Back to Rule]]'', again directed by [[Baba Yadav]], produced by [[Jaaz Multimedia]] and starring [[Jeet (actor)|Jeet]]. The film is a sequel to the 2013 film ''[[Boss: Born to Rule]]'' and also stars [[Subhasree Ganguly]]. The film is also an Indo-Bangladeshi joint venture, being co-produced by Walzen Media Works and Jeet's production company, Jeetz Filmworks.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://pressks.com/world/boss-2-movie-review-rating-good-response-makes-hit/33403/ |title=Boss 2 Movie Review, Rating - A Good Response Makes it a Hit |last=bharath |date=23 June 2017 |work=Press News Release |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> Initially rejecting the film, Faria later agreed to starring in the film when she read the script, describing her character as layered and an opportunity to show off her acting prowess, also calling the character a trendsetter.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/my-character-in-boss-2-will-be-a-trendsetter-nusraat-faria/articleshow/59250140.cms |title=My character in Boss 2 will be a trendsetter: Nusraat Faria |work=The Times of India |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> Faria also came under criticism for her costume in the music video for the song \"Rj Rock\" from ''Boss 2'', a song which was also criticized for its lyrics.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/allah-maherbaan-banned-in-bangladesh/articleshow/59095778.cms |title=Allah Maherbaan banned in Bangladesh |work=The Times of India |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref><ref name=\":5\">{{Cite news |url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/news/149455/Legal-notice-served-to-remove-Allah-Meherban |title=Legal notice served to remove 'Allah Meherban' from Youtube |work=Prothom Alo |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> The actor tried her hand at singing for a music video, 'Pataka'. Written by Rakib Rahul, the song was composed by Pritom Hasan.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://en.prothomalo.com/entertainment/news/172523/Nusrat-Faria-turns-singer |title=Nusrat Faria turns singer |work=Prothom Alo |access-date=24 March 2018 }}</ref> The music video was highly criticised by the audience, getting larger number of dislikes than likes in YouTube.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n!Co Artist\n! Notes\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|Reflist}}\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Aashiqui (2015 film)|Aashiqui]]'' || Shruti \n|[[Ankush Hazra]]|| Remake of Debut Film Telugu film ''[[Ishq (2012 film)|Ishq]]'' || <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dhallywood24.com/15843 |last=Zaman |first=Shimul |website=dhallywood24 |language=bn |script-title=bn:\u09a8\u09c1\u09b8\u09b0\u09be\u09a4 \u09ab\u09be\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b0 \u2018\u0986\u09b6\u09bf\u0995\u09bf\u2019 |trans-title=Nusrat Faria in Aashiqui |access-date=13 May 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2016 || ''[[Hero 420]]'' || Rai \n|[[Riya Sen]], Om|| Remake of Telugu film ''[[Maska (film)|Maska]]'' ||\n|-\n| ''[[Badsha: The Don]]'' || Shreya \n|[[Jeet (actor)]]|| Remake of Telugu film ''[[Don Seenu]]''\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/Tollywood-creates-history-signs-on-Jeet-for-Rs-1-crore/articleshow/50765962.cms |title=Tollywood creates history, signs on Jeet for Rs 1 crore |work=The Times of India}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2017 || ''Premi O Premi'' || \n|[[Arifin Shuvoo]]|| Bangladeshi film ||\n|-\n| ''[[Dhat Teri Ki]]'' || Shanti \n|[[Arifin Shuvoo]]|| Bangladeshi film The movie is a remake of 2012 Punjabi movie [[Carry On Jatta]]||\n|-\n|''[[Boss 2: Back to Rule]]'' || Ayesha \n|[[Jeet (actor)]]|| Sequel to ''[[Boss: Born to Rule]]'' || \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2018 || ''[[Inspector Notty K]]'' || Samira \n|[[Jeet (actor)]]|| Remake of Punjabi film ''[[Jatt & Juliet 2]]'' ||\n|-\n| ''[[Detective (2017 film)|Detective]]'' || \n|[[Arifin Shuvoo]]||[[Bangladesh]]'s first animation film. || <ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/article/665628/%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A6%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A5%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%97%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AA-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A7%9F%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%85%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%9B%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BF |script-title=bn:\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c0 \u0985\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09a8\u09bf\u09ae\u09c7\u099f\u09c7\u09a1 \u099a\u09b2\u099a\u09cd\u099a\u09bf\u09a4\u09cd\u09b0 '\u09a1\u09bf\u099f\u09c7\u0995\u099f\u09bf\u09ad' |work=Prothom Alo |language=bn}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 2019 || ''[[Bibaho Obhijaan]]'' || Rai \n|[[Ankush Hazra]]|| Indian Bengali film ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2020\n|''[[Shahenshah (2020 film)|Shahenshah]]''|| Laila\n|[[Shakib Khan]]|| ||<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/feature/2018/12/19/it-s-my-first-official-bangladeshi-film|title=Nusraat Faria: 'Shahenshah' is my first Bangladeshi film|date=19 December 2018|website=Dhaka Tribune}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Dhaka 2040'' {{dagger}} || {{TBA}} \n|[[Bappy Chowdhury]], [[Tisha (actress)]]\n|  || \n|-\n| ''Operation Sundarban''{{dagger}}|| {{TBA}} \n|[[Siam Ahmed]], [[Ziaul Roshan]]\n|  || \n|-\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\n! Title\n! Year\n! Broadcasting Station\n! Notes\n! Ref\n|-\n|''Lux Style Check''\n| 2014\n| [[Asian TV]]\n| 13 Episodes\n|\n|-\n|''Fair and Handsome: The Ultimate Man''\n|2014\n| [[Channel i]]\n| 13 Episodes\n| <ref name=\"nervous\">{{cite news |last1=Chatak |first1=Hasan |title=I'm never nervous in front of camera: Nusrat Faria |url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2014/09/04/im-never-nervous-in-front-of-camera-nusrat-faria |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune |type=Interview |access-date=13 May 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Late Night Coffee''\n|2015\n| [[Channel i]]\n| Ongoing\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Radio===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Title\n! Year\n! Broadcasting Station\n! Notes\n! Ref\n|-\n|''Night Shift with Nusrat Faria''\n||2013-2014|| [[Radio Foorti]]  || ||\n|-\n|''Love Buds''\n||2015|| [[Radio Foorti]] ||  ||\n|-\n|}\n\n== Discography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Singles\n!Name\n!Composer\n!Label\n!Year\n|-\n|Pataka\n|Pritom Hasan\n|CMV\n[[Shree Venkatesh Films|SVF Music]]\n|2018\n|}\n\n==Controversy==\nIn May 2017, Mazhar starred in the music video of \"Allah Meherbaan\", a song from her film ''[[Boss 2: Back to Rule]].'' The song then caused controversy when it was mistaken for a religious song, and resulted in a legal notice being given to [[Jaaz Multimedia]] to remove the video.<ref name=\":5\" /> Mazhar also came under criticism for wearing revealing costumes in the music video,<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/news/149697/Music-video-Allah-Meherban-removed-from-Youtube |title=Music video 'Allah Meherban' removed from Youtube |work=Prothom Alo |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> with the video being called a \"mockery of [[Islam]]\" during the month of [[Ramadan]].<ref name=\":4\" /> The video was later removed from the internet, and was later replaced by \"Yaara Meherbaan\", an updated version of the song with rewritten lyrics.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/showtime/2017/06/13/allah-meherbaan-changing-yaara-meherbaan/ |title='Allah Meherbaan' changing to 'Yaara Meherbaan' |work=Dhaka Tribune |access-date=18 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !!  Film !! Category !! Result\n!Reference(s)\n|-\n|2016|| [[Meril Prothom Alo Awards]] || ''[[Aashiqui (2015 film)|Aashiqui]]'' || Best Newcomer (Film and Television) || {{won}}\n|<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n|2017\n|[[Tele Cine Awards]]\n|''[[Badsha - The Don]]''\n|Best Actress (Bangladesh)|| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\":3\" />\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Nusrat Faria Mazhar}}\n* {{facebook|nusraatfariaofficial}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=7680133|name=Nusrat Faria}}\n* {{BMDb name | id=\u09a8\u09c1\u09b8\u09b0\u09be\u09a4-\u09ab\u09be\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be | name=Nusrat Faria}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Faria, Nusrat}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi female models]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi film actresses]]\n[[Category:Bengali television actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Bangladeshi actresses]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Bangladeshi film actress, model, television presenter and radio jockey .}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Nusrat Faria\n| image              = Nusrat Faria003.jpg\n| caption            = In 2017\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1995|09|08}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/pg/nusraatfariaofficial/about/?ref=page_internal |title=Nusraat Faria - About |website=Facebook}}</ref>\n| nationality        = [[Bangladesh]]\n| education          = [[Bachelor of Laws]] ([[LLB]])\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* Actress\n* television presenter\n* radio jockey\n* singer\n}}\n| years_active       = 2013\u2013present\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed = yes\n| background = solo_singer\n| genre = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| label = {{flatlist| \n* [[SVF Entertainment|SVF Music]]\n* CMV }}\n}}\n}}\n'''Nusrat Faria''' ({{IPA-hns|nusr\u028ct \u02c8f\u028cr\u026a\u0259|pron}}; born 1985)<ref name=nervous /> is a Bangladeshi film actress, model, television presenter and [[radio jockey]].\n\n==Early life==\nFaria had planned to be an army officer, before she became an actress.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news |last=Chaity |first=Afrose Jahan |date=4 June 2014 |title=Big screen is the place to be' |url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2014/06/03/big-screen-is-the-place-to-be |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune |access-date=13 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nFaria has started her career as a debater participating in a [[Bangladesh Television|BTV]] debate show. She is a national debate  champions in 2010 and 2011. She started her career in show business as a model in several television commercials. Throughout her career, she has worked in various [[television commercials]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://thedailynewnation.com/news/13901/nusrat-faria-in-new-tvcs.html |title=Nusrat Faria in new TVCs |date=2 June 2014 |access-date=28 May 2015 |newspaper=The New Nation}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Nusrat Faria endorsing for commercials |url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2014/12/20/nusrat-faria-endorsing-for-commercials |date=21 December 2014 |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune |access-date=28 May 2015}}</ref> and [[radio programs]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/tv/faguner-bhalobasha-channel-i-1933 |title=Faguner Bhalobasha on Channel i |date=13 February 2015 |access-date=13 May 2015 |newspaper=The Daily Star|publisher=Transcom Group }}</ref> In 2014, she hosted a reality show, ''Fair and Handsome: The Ultimate Man''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.priyo.com/2014/07/21/faria-naval-base-114749.html |title=Faria at the Naval Base |website=priyo.com |type=Blog |access-date=13 May 2015}}</ref>\nShe signed with [[Jaaz Multimedia]] to appear in two films, titled ''[[Aashiqui (2015 film)|Aashiqui]]'' and ''[[Hero 420]]''.<ref name=\":0\" /> The former, being her debut film, released in late 2015<ref>{{Cite news |title=Nusraat Faria\u2019s first hit on the movie screen |url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2015/08/15/nusraat-farias-first-hit-on-the-movie-screen |work=Dhaka Tribune |date=16 August 2015 |access-date=18 July 2017}}</ref> while the latter released in early 2016. The former also earned Faria a [[Meril Prothom Alo Awards|Meril Prothom Alo Award]] for Best Newcomer in film or television.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news |url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/news/103105/Meril-Prothom-Alo-Award-2015-conferred |title=Meril-Prothom Alo Award-2015 conferred |work=Prothom Alo |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> Both films were [[Indo-Bangla joint production|Indo-Bangladeshi joint ventures]], being co-produced by [[Eskay Movies]].\n\nIn 2016, Nusrat also starred in another Indo-Bangladeshi co-production, ''[[Badsha - The Don]]'', directed by [[Baba Yadav]]. The film also starred popular Indian actor [[Jeet (actor)|Jeet]], and is considered a turning point in Faria's career,<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news |url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/news/111647/%E2%80%98Badsha-turning-point-of-my-career%E2%80%99-Nusrat-Faria |title=\u2018Badsha', turning point of my career: Nusrat Faria |work=Prothom Alo |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> earning Faria a [[Tele Cine Awards|Tele Cine Award]] for Best Actress from Bangladesh.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/showtime/2017/05/26/razzak-conferred-lifetime-achievement-award-kolkata/ |title=Razzak conferred with a lifetime achievement award in Kolkata |work=Dhaka Tribune  |access-date=18 July 2017}}</ref>\n[[File:Nusrat Faria Mazhar.jpg|thumb|Faria hosting the grand finale of Parachute Advanced Beliphool Stylish Hair of the Campus 2014, at the [[Radisson Blu]], Dhaka Water Garden, [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh ]]]]\nAfter starring Indo-Bangladeshi films for the past two years, Faria then starred in two Bangladeshi films in 2017, ''Premi o Premi''<ref name=\":2\" /> and ''[[Dhat Teri Ki]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/showbiz/deshi-grapevine/nusrat-farias-new-mission-1351975 |title=Nusrat Faria's New Mission |date=28 January 2017 |work=The Daily Star |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> Faria also recorded dialogue for ''[[Detective (2017 film)|Detective]],'' Bangladesh's first animated film. All three of these films were produced by [[Jaaz Multimedia]] and also starred [[Arifin Shuvo]].\n\n2017 also saw Faria return with the team behind ''Badsha - The Don'' for the film ''[[Boss 2: Back to Rule]]'', again directed by [[Baba Yadav]], produced by [[Jaaz Multimedia]] and starring [[Jeet (actor)|Jeet]]. The film is a sequel to the 2013 film ''[[Boss: Born to Rule]]'' and also stars [[Subhasree Ganguly]]. The film is also an Indo-Bangladeshi joint venture, being co-produced by Walzen Media Works and Jeet's production company, Jeetz Filmworks.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://pressks.com/world/boss-2-movie-review-rating-good-response-makes-hit/33403/ |title=Boss 2 Movie Review, Rating - A Good Response Makes it a Hit |last=bharath |date=23 June 2017 |work=Press News Release |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> Initially rejecting the film, Faria later agreed to starring in the film when she read the script, describing her character as layered and an opportunity to show off her acting prowess, also calling the character a trendsetter.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/my-character-in-boss-2-will-be-a-trendsetter-nusraat-faria/articleshow/59250140.cms |title=My character in Boss 2 will be a trendsetter: Nusraat Faria |work=The Times of India |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> Faria also came under criticism for her costume in the music video for the song \"Rj Rock\" from ''Boss 2'', a song which was also criticized for its lyrics.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/allah-maherbaan-banned-in-bangladesh/articleshow/59095778.cms |title=Allah Maherbaan banned in Bangladesh |work=The Times of India |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref><ref name=\":5\">{{Cite news |url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/news/149455/Legal-notice-served-to-remove-Allah-Meherban |title=Legal notice served to remove 'Allah Meherban' from Youtube |work=Prothom Alo |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> The actor tried her hand at singing for a music video, 'Pataka'. Written by Rakib Rahul, the song was composed by Pritom Hasan.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://en.prothomalo.com/entertainment/news/172523/Nusrat-Faria-turns-singer |title=Nusrat Faria turns singer |work=Prothom Alo |access-date=24 March 2018 }}</ref> The music video was highly criticised by the audience, getting larger number of dislikes than likes in YouTube.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n!Co Artist\n! Notes\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|Reflist}}\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Aashiqui (2015 film)|Aashiqui]]'' || Shruti \n|[[Ankush Hazra]]|| Remake of Debut Film Telugu film ''[[Ishq (2012 film)|Ishq]]'' || <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dhallywood24.com/15843 |last=Zaman |first=Shimul |website=dhallywood24 |language=bn |script-title=bn:\u09a8\u09c1\u09b8\u09b0\u09be\u09a4 \u09ab\u09be\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b0 \u2018\u0986\u09b6\u09bf\u0995\u09bf\u2019 |trans-title=Nusrat Faria in Aashiqui |access-date=13 May 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2016 || ''[[Hero 420]]'' || Rai \n|[[Riya Sen]], Om|| Remake of Telugu film ''[[Maska (film)|Maska]]'' ||\n|-\n| ''[[Badsha: The Don]]'' || Shreya \n|[[Jeet (actor)]]|| Remake of Telugu film ''[[Don Seenu]]''\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/Tollywood-creates-history-signs-on-Jeet-for-Rs-1-crore/articleshow/50765962.cms |title=Tollywood creates history, signs on Jeet for Rs 1 crore |work=The Times of India}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2017 || ''Premi O Premi'' || \n|[[Arifin Shuvoo]]|| Bangladeshi film ||\n|-\n| ''[[Dhat Teri Ki]]'' || Shanti \n|[[Arifin Shuvoo]]|| Bangladeshi film The movie is a remake of 2012 Punjabi movie [[Carry On Jatta]]||\n|-\n|''[[Boss 2: Back to Rule]]'' || Ayesha \n|[[Jeet (actor)]]|| Sequel to ''[[Boss: Born to Rule]]'' || \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2018 || ''[[Inspector Notty K]]'' || Samira \n|[[Jeet (actor)]]|| Remake of Punjabi film ''[[Jatt & Juliet 2]]'' ||\n|-\n| ''[[Detective (2017 film)|Detective]]'' || \n|[[Arifin Shuvoo]]||[[Bangladesh]]'s first animation film. || <ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/article/665628/%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A6%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A5%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%97%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AA-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A7%9F%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%85%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%9B%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BF |script-title=bn:\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c0 \u0985\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09a8\u09bf\u09ae\u09c7\u099f\u09c7\u09a1 \u099a\u09b2\u099a\u09cd\u099a\u09bf\u09a4\u09cd\u09b0 '\u09a1\u09bf\u099f\u09c7\u0995\u099f\u09bf\u09ad' |work=Prothom Alo |language=bn}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 2019 || ''[[Bibaho Obhijaan]]'' || Rai \n|[[Ankush Hazra]]|| Indian Bengali film ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2020\n|''[[Shahenshah (2020 film)|Shahenshah]]''|| Laila\n|[[Shakib Khan]]|| ||<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/feature/2018/12/19/it-s-my-first-official-bangladeshi-film|title=Nusraat Faria: 'Shahenshah' is my first Bangladeshi film|date=19 December 2018|website=Dhaka Tribune}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Dhaka 2040'' {{dagger}} || {{TBA}} \n|[[Bappy Chowdhury]], [[Tisha (actress)]]\n|  || \n|-\n| ''Operation Sundarban''{{dagger}}|| {{TBA}} \n|[[Siam Ahmed]], [[Ziaul Roshan]]\n|  || \n|-\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\n! Title\n! Year\n! Broadcasting Station\n! Notes\n! Ref\n|-\n|''Lux Style Check''\n| 2014\n| [[Asian TV]]\n| 13 Episodes\n|\n|-\n|''Fair and Handsome: The Ultimate Man''\n|2014\n| [[Channel i]]\n| 13 Episodes\n| <ref name=\"nervous\">{{cite news |last1=Chatak |first1=Hasan |title=I'm never nervous in front of camera: Nusrat Faria |url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2014/09/04/im-never-nervous-in-front-of-camera-nusrat-faria |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune |type=Interview |access-date=13 May 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Late Night Coffee''\n|2015\n| [[Channel i]]\n| Ongoing\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Radio===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Title\n! Year\n! Broadcasting Station\n! Notes\n! Ref\n|-\n|''Night Shift with Nusrat Faria''\n||2013-2014|| [[Radio Foorti]]  || ||\n|-\n|''Love Buds''\n||2015|| [[Radio Foorti]] ||  ||\n|-\n|}\n\n== Discography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Singles\n!Name\n!Composer\n!Label\n!Year\n|-\n|Pataka\n|Pritom Hasan\n|CMV\n[[Shree Venkatesh Films|SVF Music]]\n|2018\n|}\n\n==Controversy==\nIn May 2017, Mazhar starred in the music video of \"Allah Meherbaan\", a song from her film ''[[Boss 2: Back to Rule]].'' The song then caused controversy when it was mistaken for a religious song, and resulted in a legal notice being given to [[Jaaz Multimedia]] to remove the video.<ref name=\":5\" /> Mazhar also came under criticism for wearing revealing costumes in the music video,<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/news/149697/Music-video-Allah-Meherban-removed-from-Youtube |title=Music video 'Allah Meherban' removed from Youtube |work=Prothom Alo |access-date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> with the video being called a \"mockery of [[Islam]]\" during the month of [[Ramadan]].<ref name=\":4\" /> The video was later removed from the internet, and was later replaced by \"Yaara Meherbaan\", an updated version of the song with rewritten lyrics.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/showtime/2017/06/13/allah-meherbaan-changing-yaara-meherbaan/ |title='Allah Meherbaan' changing to 'Yaara Meherbaan' |work=Dhaka Tribune |access-date=18 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !!  Film !! Category !! Result\n!Reference(s)\n|-\n|2016|| [[Meril Prothom Alo Awards]] || ''[[Aashiqui (2015 film)|Aashiqui]]'' || Best Newcomer (Film and Television) || {{won}}\n|<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n|2017\n|[[Tele Cine Awards]]\n|''[[Badsha - The Don]]''\n|Best Actress (Bangladesh)|| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\":3\" />\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Nusrat Faria Mazhar}}\n* {{facebook|nusraatfariaofficial}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=7680133|name=Nusrat Faria}}\n* {{BMDb name | id=\u09a8\u09c1\u09b8\u09b0\u09be\u09a4-\u09ab\u09be\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be | name=Nusrat Faria}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Faria, Nusrat}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi female models]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi film actresses]]\n[[Category:Bengali television actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Bangladeshi actresses]]\n", "name_user": "43.245.123.198", "label": "unsafe